{"type":"text","timestamp":1778696185033,"sessionID":"ses_1dd72e607ffeznJ60Rvr51ABAB","part":{"id":"prt_e228de227002X0pH2N58nzivTX","messageID":"msg_e228d8a71001R0alO1Weqn73hz","sessionID":"ses_1dd72e607ffeznJ60Rvr51ABAB","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a deliberately small micro-opt hypothesis: prune the unused `is_lui` control bit from decode and all pipeline control structs. It targets flop/fanout cleanup like the prior successful small wins, without adding CPI-changing control or touching RVFI behavior.","time":{"start":1778696184359,"end":1778696185032},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_064fa0dfcae0ee08016a04bff840ac819aa3a57ac5d3cfa007","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778696205179,"sessionID":"ses_1dd72e607ffeznJ60Rvr51ABAB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_K10efNH1UKzUlW3EbcSzXo6O","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Prune unused LUI control bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent wins came from removing always-present arithmetic, reset, and RVFI\n+  routing pressure, while broader CPI-oriented changes and control prediction\n+  usually regressed. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\n+  through decode and every pipeline stage even though LUI execution is already\n+  fully encoded by alu_op=ALU_LUI and alu_src=1. That unused bit adds one more\n+  decoded signal, pipeline flop, reset/hold mux input, and routing load across\n+  hot stage boundaries without contributing to architectural behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the redundant is_lui signal from the decoder interface and ctrl_t,\n+  and delete the corresponding ID-stage temporary and bundle assignment. Keep\n+  LUI behavior unchanged by continuing to set alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and\n+  reg_write=1 in the existing validated LUI decode arm. This is a narrow\n+  no-CPI micro-optimization that should slightly reduce control-bundle width,\n+  register enables, reset/hold muxing, and decode-to-EX routing pressure while\n+  preserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, trap discipline, memory behavior, and\n+  all existing stall/forwarding logic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unused is_lui field from ctrl_t so it no longer propagates through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB control state.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the is_lui output port and its default/LUI assignments while preserving existing LUI decode via ALU_LUI, alu_src, and reg_write.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the dec_is_lui temporary, decoder connection, and ctrl_decoded assignment that only fed the unused pipeline control bit.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Prune unused LUI control bit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent wins came from removing always-present arithmetic, reset, and RVFI\n+  routing pressure, while broader CPI-oriented changes and control prediction\n+  usually regressed. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\n+  through decode and every pipeline stage even though LUI execution is already\n+  fully encoded by alu_op=ALU_LUI and alu_src=1. That unused bit adds one more\n+  decoded signal, pipeline flop, reset/hold mux input, and routing load across\n+  hot stage boundaries without contributing to architectural behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the redundant is_lui signal from the decoder interface and ctrl_t,\n+  and delete the corresponding ID-stage temporary and bundle assignment. Keep\n+  LUI behavior unchanged by continuing to set alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and\n+  reg_write=1 in the existing validated LUI decode arm. This is a narrow\n+  no-CPI micro-optimization tha