-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Class-bit M-op encoding\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent successful micro-optimizations improved fitness by removing always-active FPGA timing and routing pressure without adding new control-flow or memory machinery. The current EX stage still detects RV32M operations with eight separate alu_op equality comparisons, and that result feeds the M-unit start/busy path, redirect suppression, and EX/MEM bubble control. CoreMark rarely benefits from complex M-op detection logic being on this hot execute-control path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Recode the internal ALU operation constants so every RV32M operation has alu_op[4]=1 while all ordinary RV32I operations keep alu_op[4]=0. Then replace the EX-stage is_m_op eight-way compare tree with a single in.valid && in.ctrl.alu_op[4] test. This preserves the decoder's legal-instruction checks, ALU and M-unit case behavior, RVFI retirement, and the existing one-cycle M-unit handshake, but should reduce LUT depth and fanout in the execute control path with no CPI cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Reassign ALU_MUL through ALU_REMU localparams into a contiguous high-bit class while leaving RV32I ALU ops below bit 4.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the explicit eight-operation is_m_op comparison with a single alu_op class-bit check.\"\n","additions":15,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778697831222,"end":1778697831224}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ffbfc9e41ccf10f016a04c658984c819b9d8d7197797b1997"}},"id":"prt_e22a6ca8c001U6lpTmaPCuYGij","sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab9d1ffe2B2A54E2vq8V30","messageID":"msg_e22a6afeb001w92K0TFdS79Xg2"}}
