{"type":"text","timestamp":1778698729780,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","part":{"id":"prt_e22b4b51a001BAThkVWOq36k6J","messageID":"msg_e22b49412001rTYfHnSIyrtRML","sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","type":"text","text":"The log confirms prior successful micro-opts were narrow removals of always-active routing or arithmetic pressure; recent attempts to add prediction, bypassing, or further payload/control splitting regressed. I’m selecting a single low-risk cleanup that removes redundant control state rather than adding new pipeline behavior.","time":{"start":1778698728730,"end":1778698729780},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_090c2ae4b18c127d016a04c9e87050819badd2f56fdd5438d6","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778698731986,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4Z8E8GMQ3t9q2s0AdtgtWhcL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","offset":29,"limit":3},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n29: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\", \"title\": \"Prune unused LUI control bit\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"Recent wins came from removing always-present arithmetic, reset, and RVFI\\nrouting pressure, while broader CPI-oriented changes and control prediction\\nusually regressed. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\\nthrough decode and every pipeline stage even though LUI execution is already\\nfully encoded by alu_op=ALU_LUI and alu_src=1. That unused bit adds one more\\ndecoded signal, pipeline flop, reset/hold mux input, and routing load across\\nhot stage boundaries without contributing to architectural behavior.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Recent wins came from removing always-present arithmetic, reset, and RVFI\\nrouting pressure, while broader CPI-oriented changes and control prediction\\nusually regressed. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\\nthrough decode and every pipeline stage even though LUI execution is already\\nfully encoded by alu_op=ALU_LUI and alu_src=1. That unused bit adds one more\\ndecoded signal, pipeline flop, reset/hold mux input, and routing load across\\nhot stage boundaries without contributing to architectural behavior.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the redundant is_lui signal from the decoder interface and ctrl_t,\\nand delete the corresponding ID-stage temporary and bundle assignment. Keep\\nLUI behavior unchanged by continuing to set alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and\\nreg_write=1 in the existing validated LUI decode arm. This is a narrow\\nno-CPI micro-optimization that should slightly reduce control-bundle width,\\nregister enables, reset/hold muxing, and decode-to-EX routing pressure while\\npreserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, trap discipline, memory behavior, and\\nall existing stall/forwarding logic.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 1, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the unused is_lui field from ctrl_t so it no longer propagates throug... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n30: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r10s1\", \"title\": \"Split MEM RVFI sideband path\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The latest successful structural change split RVFI-only metadata away from the hot execution payloads and improved fitness without changing CPI. The remaining MEM stage still computes and registers RVFI memory sideband fields in the same combinational block and pipeline boundary that drives dmem, load extraction, writeback, and forwarding. A narrower structural separation in MEM is a safer follow-on than adding predictors, store buffers, load bypasses, or deeper execute retiming, all of which have regressed or broken previously.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The latest successful structural change split RVFI-only metadata away from the hot execution payloads and improved fitness without changing CPI. The remaining MEM stage still computes and registers RVFI memory sideband fields in the same combinational block and pipeline boundary that drives dmem, load extraction, writeback, and forwarding. A narrower structural separation in MEM is a safer follow-on than adding predictors, store buffers, load bypasses, or deeper execute retiming, all of which have regressed or broken previously.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Split the MEM-stage memory sideband work into a parallel RVFI-only path while keeping the execution path limited to dmem request signals, load_data, rd, compact control, and valid. The hot MEM/WB execution register should no longer share bundle assignment, hold, and mux fanout with RVFI-only mem_addr, mem_rmask, mem_wmask, mem_rdata, mem_wdata, pc, source values, and instruction fields. Preserve the existing single-retire MEM/WB retirement point, dmem stall behavior, misalignment traps, RVFI aligned-memory reporting, and NRET=1 port shape. This should reduce routing and enable fanout around the MEM boundary with little CPI risk, extending the proven RVFI-shadow split into the last stage where sideband metadata still sits next to timing-sensitive load/w... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n31: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\", \"title\": \"Single hot loop branch predictor\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added immediate\\ndecode, target adders, return-stack state, counters, or multi-entry tag logic\\nto the fetch/decode control paths. CoreMark still spends cycles on repeated\\ntaken loop-closing branches, but the predictor must be smaller than the prior\\nBTB, RAS, JAL, and decode-backward experiments to have any chance of paying\\non Tang Nano 20K fitness.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added immediate\\ndecode, target adders, return-stack state, counters, or multi-entry tag logic\\nto the fetch/decode control paths. CoreMark still spends cycles on repeated\\ntaken loop-closing branches, but the predictor must be smaller than the prior\\nBTB, RAS, JAL, and decode-backward experiments to have any chance of paying\\non Tang Nano 20K fitness.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add the smallest possible EX-trained predictor for one hot taken conditional\\nbranch: store a single branch PC and its already-resolved target when EX sees\\na taken backward branch, predict that target only on an exact PC match, and\\ninvalidate the entry when the same branch later resolves not-taken. Unlike the\\nfailed BTFNT and BTB attempts, IF performs no instruction immediate decode and\\nno target addition; it only compares the current PC with one registered PC and\\nmuxes between pc+4 and one registered target. Carry a one-bit predicted flag\\nand predicted next PC to EX so correct predictions suppress the normal taken\\nredirect while mismatches use the existing recovery path. This targets the most\\ncommon loop bubble with minimal predictor state and avoids JAL/JALR/RAS logic.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 1, \"confidence\": \"low\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX b... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(Showing lines 29-31 of 37. Use offset=32 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\", \"title\": \"Prune unused LUI control bit\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"Recent wins came from removing always-present arithmetic, reset, and RVFI\\nrouting pressure, while broader CPI-oriented changes and control prediction\\nusually regressed. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\\nthrough decode and every pipeline stage even though LUI execution is already\\nfully encoded by alu_op=ALU_LUI and alu_src=1. That unused bit adds one more\\ndecoded signal, pipeline flop, reset/hold mux input, and routing load across\\nhot stage boundaries without contributing to architectural behavior.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Recent wins came from removing always-present arithmetic, reset, and RVFI\\nrouting pressure, while broader CPI-oriented changes and control prediction\\nusually regressed. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\\nthrough decode and every pipeline stage even though LUI execution is already\\nfully encoded by alu_op=ALU_LUI and alu_src=1. That unused bit adds one more\\ndecoded signal, pipeline flop, reset/hold mux input, and routing load across\\nhot stage boundaries without contributing to architectural behavior.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Remove the redundant is_lui signal from the decoder interface and ctrl_t,\\nand delete the corresponding ID-stage temporary and bundle assignment. Keep\\nLUI behavior unchanged by continuing to set alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and\\nreg_write=1 in the existing validated LUI decode arm. This is a narrow\\nno-CPI micro-optimization that should slightly reduce control-bundle width,\\nregister enables, reset/hold muxing, and decode-to-EX routing pressure while\\npreserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, trap discipline, memory behavior, and\\nall existing stall/forwarding logic.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 1, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove the unused is_lui field from ctrl_t so it no longer propagates throug... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r10s1\", \"title\": \"Split MEM RVFI sideband path\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The latest successful structural change split RVFI-only metadata away from the hot execution payloads and improved fitness without changing CPI. The remaining MEM stage still computes and registers RVFI memory sideband fields in the same combinational block and pipeline boundary that drives dmem, load extraction, writeback, and forwarding. A narrower structural separation in MEM is a safer follow-on than adding predictors, store buffers, load bypasses, or deeper execute retiming, all of which have regressed or broken previously.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The latest successful structural change split RVFI-only metadata away from the hot execution payloads and improved fitness without changing CPI. The remaining MEM stage still computes and registers RVFI memory sideband fields in the same combinational block and pipeline boundary that drives dmem, load extraction, writeback, and forwarding. A narrower structural separation in MEM is a safer follow-on than adding predictors, store buffers, load bypasses, or deeper execute retiming, all of which have regressed or broken previously.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Split the MEM-stage memory sideband work into a parallel RVFI-only path while keeping the execution path limited to dmem request signals, load_data, rd, compact control, and valid. The hot MEM/WB execution register should no longer share bundle assignment, hold, and mux fanout with RVFI-only mem_addr, mem_rmask, mem_wmask, mem_rdata, mem_wdata, pc, source values, and instruction fields. Preserve the existing single-retire MEM/WB retirement point, dmem stall behavior, misalignment traps, RVFI aligned-memory reporting, and NRET=1 port shape. This should reduce routing and enable fanout around the MEM boundary with little CPI risk, extending the proven RVFI-shadow split into the last stage where sideband metadata still sits next to timing-sensitive load/w... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\", \"title\": \"Single hot loop branch predictor\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added immediate\\ndecode, target adders, return-stack state, counters, or multi-entry tag logic\\nto the fetch/decode control paths. CoreMark still spends cycles on repeated\\ntaken loop-closing branches, but the predictor must be smaller than the prior\\nBTB, RAS, JAL, and decode-backward experiments to have any chance of paying\\non Tang Nano 20K fitness.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added immediate\\ndecode, target adders, return-stack state, counters, or multi-entry tag logic\\nto the fetch/decode control paths. CoreMark still spends cycles on repeated\\ntaken loop-closing branches, but the predictor must be smaller than the prior\\nBTB, RAS, JAL, and decode-backward experiments to have any chance of paying\\non Tang Nano 20K fitness.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add the smallest possible EX-trained predictor for one hot taken conditional\\nbranch: store a single branch PC and its already-resolved target when EX sees\\na taken backward branch, predict that target only on an exact PC match, and\\ninvalidate the entry when the same branch later resolves not-taken. Unlike the\\nfailed BTFNT and BTB attempts, IF performs no instruction immediate decode and\\nno target addition; it only compares the current PC with one registered PC and\\nmuxes between pc+4 and one registered target. Carry a one-bit predicted flag\\nand predicted next PC to EX so correct predictions suppress the normal taken\\nredirect while mismatches use the existing recovery path. This targets the most\\ncommon loop bubble with minimal predictor state and avoids JAL/JALR/RAS logic.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 1, \"confidence\": \"low\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX b... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778698731983,"end":1778698731985}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_090c2ae4b18c127d016a04c9e9acb8819b839fe5e538b19c78"}},"id":"prt_e22b4b935001ZM0gPMGG9kodpo","sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","messageID":"msg_e22b49412001rTYfHnSIyrtRML"}}
