{"type":"text","timestamp":1778698771598,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","part":{"id":"prt_e22b557ef001l5XG02hiuu9AFu","messageID":"msg_e22b5340d001YKHFoXqhgz89z8","sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a narrow `is_lui` control-bit pruning proposal. It only removes a redundant decoded bit from the hot control bundle; LUI remains encoded by `ALU_LUI`, `alu_src`, and `reg_write`.","time":{"start":1778698770415,"end":1778698771597},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0526181f948498b2016a04ca124980819aa74242e4224d93b1","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778698789277,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_XaoO7URVJkVDNNG1E5h1dfLl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Prune redundant LUI control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest bench-core results have come from removing always-active FPGA\n+  routing pressure without adding new prediction, bypass, memory ordering, or\n+  retiming machinery. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\n+  from decode through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB even though no live execute,\n+  memory, writeback, hazard, or RVFI logic consumes it. LUI behavior is already\n+  fully represented by alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and reg_write=1.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the redundant is_lui signal from ctrl_t and from the decoder and ID\n+  stage wiring, leaving the existing LUI decode arm to set ALU_LUI, alu_src,\n+  and reg_write exactly as before. This should slightly reduce control-bundle\n+  width, pipeline register muxing, and decode-to-execute routing fanout with no\n+  CPI cost and no change to the NRET=1 top-level RVFI contract. The change is\n+  intentionally smaller than the regressed control-payload splits and avoids\n+  all front-end predictor or memory-bypass paths that have repeatedly lost\n+  fitness on this FPGA.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unused is_lui field from ctrl_t so it no longer propagates through pipeline payloads.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the is_lui output and keep the validated LUI arm encoded through ALU_LUI, alu_src, and reg_write.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the dec_is_lui temporary, decoder connection, and ctrl_decoded assignment.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Prune redundant LUI control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest bench-core results have come from removing always-active FPGA\n+  routing pressure without adding new prediction, bypass, memory ordering, or\n+  retiming machinery. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\n+  from decode through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB even though no live execute,\n+  memory, writeback, hazard, or RVFI logic consumes it. LUI behavior is already\n+  fully represented by alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and reg_write=1.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the redundant is_lui signal from ctrl_t and from the decoder and ID\n+  stage wiring, leaving the existing LUI decode arm to set ALU_LUI, alu_src,\n+  and reg_write exactly as before. This should slightly reduce control-bundle\n+  width, pipeline register muxing, and decode-to-execute routing fanout with no\n+  CPI cost and no change to the NRET=1 top-level RVFI contract. The change is\n+  intentionally smaller than the regressed control-payload splits and avoids\n+  all front-end predictor or memory-bypass paths that have repeatedly lost\n+  fitness on this FPGA.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the unused is_lui field from ctrl_t so it no longer propagates through pipeline payloads.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the is_lui output and keep the validated LUI arm encoded through ALU_LUI, alu_src, and reg_write.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the dec_is_lui temporary, decoder connection, and ctrl_decoded assignment.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Prune redundant LUI control\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest bench-core results have come from removing always-active FPGA\n+  routing pressure without adding new prediction, bypass, memory ordering, or\n+  retiming machinery. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\n+  from decode through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB even though no live execute,\n+  memory, writeback, hazard, or RVFI logic consumes it. LUI behavior is already\n+  fully represented by alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and reg_write=1.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the redundant is_lui signal from ctrl_t and from the decoder and ID\n+  stage wiring, leaving the existing LUI decode arm to set ALU_LUI, alu_src,\n+  and reg_write exactly as before. This s