 it no longer propagates through pipeline payloads.\"\n26:   - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n27:     description: \"Drop the is_lui output and keep the validated LUI arm encoded through ALU_LUI, alu_src, and reg_write.\"\n28:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n29:     description: \"Remove the dec_is_lui temporary, decoder connection, and ctrl_decoded assignment.\"\n\n(End of file - total 29 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r13s0\ntitle: \"Prune redundant LUI control\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The strongest bench-core results have come from removing always-active FPGA\n  routing pressure without adding new prediction, bypass, memory ordering, or\n  retiming machinery. The current control bundle still carries an is_lui bit\n  from decode through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB even though no live execute,\n  memory, writeback, hazard, or RVFI logic consumes it. LUI behavior is already\n  fully represented by alu_op=ALU_LUI, alu_src=1, and reg_write=1.\nhypothesis: |\n  Remove the redundant is_lui signal from ctrl_t and from the decoder and ID\n  stage wiring, leaving the existing LUI decode arm to set ALU_LUI, alu_src,\n  and reg_write exactly as before. This should slightly reduce control-bundle\n  width, pipeline register muxing, and decode-to-execute routing fanout with no\n  CPI cost and no change to the NRET=1 top-level RVFI contract. The change is\n  intentionally smaller than the regressed control-payload splits and avoids\n  all front-end predictor or memory-bypass paths that have repeatedly lost\n  fitness on this FPGA.\nexpected_impact:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r13s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778698794899,"end":1778698794907}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0496c64342673b46016a04ca2971f8819895b7b4838b417b3d"}},"id":"prt_e22b5b257001oA1L0BS6Q13MVz","sessionID":"ses_1dd4b964cffeq9qZa6LGSGNehP","messageID":"msg_e22b5a27c001Rzr9eeoEVdUPHH"}}
