{"type":"text","timestamp":1778677721993,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c31cdffeUUuxJASrZ4bNkX","part":{"id":"prt_e21742a39001d8SJ37b9eKONw1","messageID":"msg_e21741246002BZVWRE6tgelg7x","sessionID":"ses_1de8c31cdffeUUuxJASrZ4bNkX","type":"text","text":"No curated lessons exist and the only logged `micro_opt` entry is the baseline retest, so there is no negative prior result to avoid. The strongest low-risk micro-opt target is the always-active RV32M divider/multiplier cone in the combinational ALU, which likely taxes Fmax even though CoreMark rarely benefits from single-cycle divide.","time":{"start":1778677721657,"end":1778677721990},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_063f4bc470619bc8016a0477d988ac819bb004eedb910a7d54","phase":"commentary"}}}}
