{"type":"text","timestamp":1778677729914,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c31cdffeUUuxJASrZ4bNkX","part":{"id":"prt_e217442a1001JKlfKv1Q8NwpzF","messageID":"msg_e21743787001toDmWlGozc2BHq","sessionID":"ses_1de8c31cdffeUUuxJASrZ4bNkX","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a hypothesis focused on replacing the expensive combinational RV32M arithmetic cone with a small multicycle M-unit interface while preserving RVFI retirement semantics and the existing single-retire contract.","time":{"start":1778677727905,"end":1778677729911},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0eae1681ec54c2bf016a0477dfcee48199a3f04e1e26006429","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778677753981,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c31cdffeUUuxJASrZ4bNkX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_lQ58Gp1JGWrF7CNVlR9PtLs2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Multicycle RV32M arithmetic unit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU computes every multiply and divide result combinationally in\n+  the EX stage, including signed and unsigned 64-bit products plus divider and\n+  remainder operators. That wide arithmetic cone is a likely Fmax limiter on\n+  Tang Nano 20K, while CoreMark's hot path should not need single-cycle DIV/REM\n+  throughput. Trading rare M-extension latency for a shorter common EX critical\n+  path should improve iterations/second through higher clock frequency.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split RV32M operations out of the always-combinational ALU path behind a\n+  small multicycle M-unit handshake in EX. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/branch/address\n+  operations purely combinational, but when the decoded alu_op is MUL/DIV/REM,\n+  hold ID/EX and EX/MEM until the iterative arithmetic result is ready, then\n+  retire normally through the existing MEM/WB and RVFI path. This should remove\n+  divider and large multiplier logic from the ordinary EX-stage timing path;\n+  the added stalls only affect uncommon M instructions and should be outweighed\n+  by improved Fmax on the FPGA fitness metric.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Restrict the combinational ALU to fast RV32I operations and expose only lightweight M-op selection or helper logic needed by the new M-unit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a multicycle RV32M execution path that stalls EX until the M result is valid while preserving forwarding, branch resolution, and RVFI data fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX-stage multicycle busy input so the pipeline holds cleanly during M-unit execution without double retirement or lost redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX-stage M-unit busy/hold signal into the existing stall network without changing the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any minimal control/type bits needed to identify multicycle M operations while leaving decoder illegality rules unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adjust ALU/M-unit cocotb vectors to prove RV32M exact results still match the existing arithmetic contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Multicycle RV32M arithmetic unit\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU computes every multiply and divide result combinationally in\n+  the EX stage, including signed and unsigned 64-bit products plus divider and\n+  remainder operators. That wide arithmetic cone is a likely Fmax limiter on\n+  Tang Nano 20K, while CoreMark's hot path should not need single-cycle DIV/REM\n+  throughput. Trading rare M-extension latency for a shorter common EX critical\n+  path should improve iterations/second through higher clock frequency.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split RV32M operations out of the always-combinational ALU path behind a\n+  small multicycle M-unit handshake in EX. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/branch/address\n+  operations purely combinational, but when the decoded alu_op is MUL/DIV/REM,\n+  hold ID/EX and EX/MEM until the iterative arithmetic result is ready, then\n+  retire normally through the existing MEM/WB and RVFI path. This should remove\n+  divider and large multiplier logic from the ordinary EX-stage timing path;\n+  the added stalls only affect uncommon M instructions and should be outweighed\n+  by improved Fmax on the FPGA fitness metric.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Restrict the combinational ALU to fast RV32I operations and expose only lightweight M-op selection or helper logic needed by the new M-unit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a multicycle RV32M execution path that stalls EX until the M result is valid while preserving forwarding, branch resolution, and RVFI data fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX-stage multicycle busy input so the pipeline holds cleanly during M-unit execution without double retirement or lost redirects.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX-stage M-unit busy/hold signal into the existing stall network without changing the nret=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add any minimal control/type bits needed to identify multicycle M operations while leaving decoder illegality rules unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or adjust ALU/M-unit cocotb vectors to prove RV32M exact results still match the existing arithmetic contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/