{"type":"text","timestamp":1778678982933,"sessionID":"ses_1de794152ffeQ1ahYrM2u1ppVx","part":{"id":"prt_e21876891001CxWyx99zGm5eKV","messageID":"msg_e21872198001hi0pHzeWV4SHme","sessionID":"ses_1de794152ffeQ1ahYrM2u1ppVx","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a focused hypothesis to replace MEM-stage variable shifts/masks with small fixed case muxes. This targets Fmax and LUT pressure on the load-data path without changing pipeline behavior or retirement semantics.","time":{"start":1778678982801,"end":1778678982933},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_000c2d8188a23dd7016a047cc6a59c8198887d3c1a99edc6ac","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778678996626,"sessionID":"ses_1de794152ffeQ1ahYrM2u1ppVx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_X5rEcUeVGy9XPoGj37BKHmSk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: Simplify MEM load lane muxes\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  After the successful M-unit split, the remaining always-active timing paths are more likely to be ordinary RV32I datapath logic than rare multiply/divide arithmetic. The MEM stage currently uses variable shifts for load extraction and shifted masks for byte lanes, which can synthesize into wider mux/barrel-shifter logic on the FPGA load-to-WB path. CoreMark performs many byte, halfword, and word accesses, so a smaller MEM-stage cone should improve Fmax without changing CPI.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the MEM-stage byte-lane handling as explicit case muxes keyed by addr[1:0] instead of expressions like dmem_rdata >> (addr[1:0] * 8) and mask << addr[1:0]. Keep the same misalignment trap behavior, RVFI aligned mem_addr reporting, replicated store data convention, and MEM/WB retirement boundary. This should reduce LUT depth and routing on the common load-data path while preserving the existing five-stage control flow and single-retire NRET=1 contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace variable load-data shifts and shifted byte masks with explicit addr[1:0] case muxes for LB/LBU/LH/LHU/LW and store masks.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r2s0\n+title: Simplify MEM load lane muxes\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  After the successful M-unit split, the remaining always-active timing paths are more likely to be ordinary RV32I datapath logic than rare multiply/divide arithmetic. The MEM stage currently uses variable shifts for load extraction and shifted masks for byte lanes, which can synthesize into wider mux/barrel-shifter logic on the FPGA load-to-WB path. CoreMark performs many byte, halfword, and word accesses, so a smaller MEM-stage cone should improve Fmax without changing CPI.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the MEM-stage byte-lane handling as explicit case muxes keyed by addr[1:0] instead of expressions like dmem_rdata >> (addr[1:0] * 8) and mask << addr[1:0]. Keep the same misalignment trap behavior, RVFI aligned mem_addr reporting, replicated store data convention, and MEM/WB retirement boundary. This should reduce LUT depth and routing on the common load-data path while preserving the existing five-stage control flow and single-retire NRET=1 contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace variable load-data shifts and shifted byte masks with explicit addr[1:0] case muxes for LB/LBU/LH/LHU/LW and store masks.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r2s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.cla