{"type":"text","timestamp":1778680483471,"sessionID":"ses_1de624b58ffeP8d5kAORx3UNW9","part":{"id":"prt_e219e4457001uQuYzzqwb4G25I","messageID":"msg_e219ddf41001xIpduA2kOIQ8Ih","sessionID":"ses_1de624b58ffeP8d5kAORx3UNW9","type":"text","text":"Prior `micro_opt` results show the big win was removing M arithmetic from the EX critical path, while a MEM lane rewrite slightly regressed. I’m choosing a narrower CPI-oriented micro-optimization: eliminate false load-use stalls by making hazard detection source-aware instead of treating every instruction’s `rs2` bitfield as a real source.","time":{"start":1778680480855,"end":1778680483470},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ad387a1ebc82008016a0482a0b9a88199bbb77db182d7e16d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778680499898,"sessionID":"ses_1de624b58ffeP8d5kAORx3UNW9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_HVH16OLXTJZA1YXeoY2C21Io","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Source-aware load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use hazard detector compares a load destination against the\n+  raw rs1 and rs2 bitfields of the following instruction, regardless of whether\n+  that instruction actually consumes those operands. For I-type immediates,\n+  loads, JALR, LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and EBREAK, some of those fields are\n+  immediates or destination bits rather than true sources. Any accidental match\n+  with the preceding load rd inserts an unnecessary bubble, directly reducing\n+  CoreMark iterations per cycle without improving correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make the load-use interlock source-aware by qualifying the rd comparisons with\n+  simple decoded uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 signals for the instruction currently in\n+  IF/ID. Keep the existing one-cycle stall for real load consumers, but avoid\n+  stalling on unused source fields such as OP-IMM rs2 bits, U/J-type operand\n+  fields, and SYSTEM/FENCE encodings. This should improve CPI under CoreMark's\n+  load-heavy code while adding only small opcode decode logic off the main ALU\n+  and memory datapaths, so Fmax should be largely preserved.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Derive or wire IF/ID source-use qualifiers into the hazard unit without changing the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate load-use rd comparisons with uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 so only real source operands trigger the interlock.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Source-aware load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use hazard detector compares a load destination against the\n+  raw rs1 and rs2 bitfields of the following instruction, regardless of whether\n+  that instruction actually consumes those operands. For I-type immediates,\n+  loads, JALR, LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and EBREAK, some of those fields are\n+  immediates or destination bits rather than true sources. Any accidental match\n+  with the preceding load rd inserts an unnecessary bubble, directly reducing\n+  CoreMark iterations per cycle without improving correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make the load-use interlock source-aware by qualifying the rd comparisons with\n+  simple decoded uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 signals for the instruction currently in\n+  IF/ID. Keep the existing one-cycle stall for real load consumers, but avoid\n+  stalling on unused source fields such as OP-IMM rs2 bits, U/J-type operand\n+  fields, and SYSTEM/FENCE encodings. This should improve CPI under CoreMark's\n+  load-heavy code while adding only small opcode decode logic off the main ALU\n+  and memory datapaths, so Fmax should be largely preserved.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Derive or wire IF/ID source-use qualifiers into the hazard unit without changing the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate load-use rd comparisons with uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 so only real source operands trigger the interlock.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Source-aware load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use hazard detector compares a load destination against the\n+  raw rs1 and rs2 bitfields of the following instruction, regardless of whether\n+  that instruction actually consumes those operands. For I-type immediates,\n+  loads, JALR, LUI, AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, and EBREAK, some of those fields are\n+  immediates or destination bits rather than true sources. Any accidental match\n+  with the preceding load rd inserts an unnecessary bubble, directly reducing\n+  CoreMark iterations per cycle without improving correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Make the load-use interlock source-aware by qualifying the rd comparisons with\n+  simple decoded uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 signals for the instruction currently in\n+  IF/ID. Keep the existing one-cycle stall for real load consumers, but avoid\n+  stalling on unused source fields such as OP-IMM rs2 bits, U/J-type operand\n+  fields, and SYSTEM/FENCE encodings. This should improve CPI under CoreMark's\n+  load-heavy code while adding only small opcode decode logic off the main ALU\n+  and memory datapaths, so Fmax should be largely preserved.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Derive or wire IF/ID source-use qualifiers into the hazard unit without changing the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate load-use rd comparisons with uses_rs1 and uses_rs2 so only real source operands trigger the interlock.\"\n","additions":27,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778680499895,"end":1778680499897}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ad387a1ebc82008016a0482a3555081999181be429aa47e18"}},"id":"prt_e219e4e9e0012a6uJ8O3QOSC9b","sessionID":"ses_1de624b58ffeP8d5kAORx3UNW9","messageID":"msg_e219ddf41001xIpduA2kOIQ8Ih"}}
