{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778687348109,"sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c34effe5cNbQHQiUjgtac","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_NVo9oju352IYnjZuqEqzMZu4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune dead EX/MEM branch metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already won most of its fitness from removing broad\n+  timing/fanout costs, while recent attempts that add prediction, buffering,\n+  bypassing, or memory-ordering control have regressed. The EX/MEM bundle still\n+  carries branch_taken and branch_target fields that are assigned every cycle\n+  but are not consumed by MEM, WB, RVFI, hazard, or forwarding logic. Those 33\n+  dead flops and their input adders/mux routes sit in an always-active pipeline\n+  boundary, so pruning them is a low-risk micro-optimization for LUT/FF count\n+  and routing delay without changing CPI.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from ex_mem_t and stop\n+  registering them in ex_stage. Keep redirect and pc_next computation exactly as\n+  they are today, because pc_next is the RVFI-visible resolved next PC and the\n+  redirect output is still the only live control-flow signal. This should trim\n+  dead sequential state and reduce EX-stage fanout/routing pressure while\n+  preserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, trap behavior, memory behavior, and all\n+  existing stall/flush priorities.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from the EX/MEM pipeline bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop assigning the removed EX/MEM branch metadata while leaving redirect and pc_next logic unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune dead EX/MEM branch metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already won most of its fitness from removing broad\n+  timing/fanout costs, while recent attempts that add prediction, buffering,\n+  bypassing, or memory-ordering control have regressed. The EX/MEM bundle still\n+  carries branch_taken and branch_target fields that are assigned every cycle\n+  but are not consumed by MEM, WB, RVFI, hazard, or forwarding logic. Those 33\n+  dead flops and their input adders/mux routes sit in an always-active pipeline\n+  boundary, so pruning them is a low-risk micro-optimization for LUT/FF count\n+  and routing delay without changing CPI.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from ex_mem_t and stop\n+  registering them in ex_stage. Keep redirect and pc_next computation exactly as\n+  they are today, because pc_next is the RVFI-visible resolved next PC and the\n+  redirect output is still the only live control-flow signal. This should trim\n+  dead sequential state and reduce EX-stage fanout/routing pressure while\n+  preserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, trap behavior, memory behavior, and all\n+  existing stall/flush priorities.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from the EX/MEM pipeline bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop assigning the removed EX/MEM branch metadata while leaving redirect and pc_next logic unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune dead EX/MEM branch metadata\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core has already won most of its fitness from removing broad\n+  timing/fanout costs, while recent attempts that add prediction, buffering,\n+  bypassing, or memory-ordering control have regressed. The EX/MEM bundle still\n+  carries branch_taken and branch_target fields that are assigned every cycle\n+  but are not consumed by MEM, WB, RVFI, hazard, or forwarding logic. Those 33\n+  dead flops and their input adders/mux routes sit in an always-active pipeline\n+  boundary, so pruning them is a low-risk micro-optimization for LUT/FF count\n+  and routing delay without changing CPI.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove the unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from ex_mem_t and stop\n+  registering them in ex_stage. Keep redirect and pc_next computation exactly as\n+  they are today, because pc_next is the RVFI-visible resolved next PC and the\n+  redirect output is still the only live control-flow signal. This should trim\n+  dead sequential state and reduce EX-stage fanout/routing pressure while\n+  preserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, trap behavior, memory behavior, and all\n+  existing stall/flush priorities.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused branch_taken and branch_target fields from the EX/MEM pipeline bundle.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop assigning the removed EX/MEM branch metadata while leaving redirect and pc_next logic unchanged.\"\n","additions":28,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778687348102,"end":1778687348108}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_020dcae227aa6970016a049d626ea4819a9bb47dc9d039e589"}},"id":"prt_e2206c8ec001IyqItA74lmpJ3l","sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c34effe5cNbQHQiUjgtac","messageID":"msg_e2206bfbf001acbmX90lwLS0fA"}}
