{"type":"text","timestamp":1778689136790,"sessionID":"ses_1ddde3f62ffe7ptYFGvwU9A50r","part":{"id":"prt_e222251010015UFP3OVxoM3ZYw","messageID":"msg_e2221f49d0010SCFoZqbR1fW5v","sessionID":"ses_1ddde3f62ffe7ptYFGvwU9A50r","type":"text","text":"Prior micro-opt wins came from removing broad datapath costs, especially RV32M arithmetic, while later small control/data-path edits mostly regressed. The strongest remaining micro-opt angle is to take the current one-cycle `m_unit` further by removing combinational divider/remainder hardware from the FPGA timing graph with a true iterative DIV/REM path, keeping ordinary RV32I and MUL behavior unchanged.","time":{"start":1778689134849,"end":1778689136788},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_018b93804a2968cc016a04a46ebd70819b924e4e9802fc1e4e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778689154010,"sessionID":"ses_1ddde3f62ffe7ptYFGvwU9A50r","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cUI3BVDO3ANphVqsSyQLxxoV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Iterative M divider\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The largest proven fitness gain for this core came from moving RV32M arithmetic\n+  out of the ordinary EX ALU path, but the current m_unit still contains wide\n+  combinational DIV/REM operators behind a one-cycle result register. Even if\n+  those operations are rare in CoreMark, the FPGA still has to place and time\n+  the divider/remainder cone, so it can cap Fmax or perturb routing for the hot\n+  RV32I pipeline.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the one-cycle DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU implementation in m_unit with a small\n+  iterative restoring divider that runs only after a divide or remainder starts.\n+  Keep MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU on the existing short registered path so any\n+  multiply use does not pay a 32-cycle penalty, and keep the existing EX-stage\n+  hold/valid handshake as the only pipeline interface. This should remove the\n+  expensive combinational divider/remainder logic from the FPGA timing closure\n+  problem while adding CPI only for uncommon divide/remainder instructions.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Implement DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with an iterative signed/unsigned divider state machine while preserving ALTOPS behavior under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust the existing M-unit busy/valid handshake only as needed so EX holds until multi-cycle DIV/REM completion and still clears completed results exactly once.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Iterative M divider\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The largest proven fitness gain for this core came from moving RV32M arithmetic\n+  out of the ordinary EX ALU path, but the current m_unit still contains wide\n+  combinational DIV/REM operators behind a one-cycle result register. Even if\n+  those operations are rare in CoreMark, the FPGA still has to place and time\n+  the divider/remainder cone, so it can cap Fmax or perturb routing for the hot\n+  RV32I pipeline.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the one-cycle DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU implementation in m_unit with a small\n+  iterative restoring divider that runs only after a divide or remainder starts.\n+  Keep MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU on the existing short registered path so any\n+  multiply use does not pay a 32-cycle penalty, and keep the existing EX-stage\n+  hold/valid handshake as the only pipeline interface. This should remove the\n+  expensive combinational divider/remainder logic from the FPGA timing closure\n+  problem while adding CPI only for uncommon divide/remainder instructions.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Implement DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with an iterative signed/unsigned divider state machine while preserving ALTOPS behavior under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust the existing M-unit busy/valid handshake only as needed so EX holds until multi-cycle DIV/REM completion and still clears completed results exactly once.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Iterative M divider\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The largest proven fitness gain for this core came from moving RV32M arithmetic\n+  out of the ordinary EX ALU path, but the current m_unit still contains wide\n+  combinational DIV/REM operators behind a one-cycle result register. Even if\n+  those operations are rare in CoreMark, the FPGA still has to place and time\n+  the divider/remainder cone, so it can cap Fmax or perturb routing for the hot\n+  RV32I pipeline.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the one-cycle DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU implementation in m_unit with a small\n+  iterative restoring divider that runs only after a divide or remainder starts.\n+  Keep MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU on the existing short registered path so any\n+  multiply use does not pay a 32-cycle penalty, and keep the existing EX-stage\n+  hold/valid handshake as the only pipeline interface. This should remove the\n+  expensive combinational divider/remainder logic from the FPGA timing closure\n+  problem while adding CPI only for uncommon divide/remainder instructions.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Implement DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with an iterative signed/unsigned divider state machine while preserving ALTOPS behavior under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust the existing M-unit busy/valid handshake only as needed so EX holds until multi-cycle DIV/REM completion and still clears completed results exactly once.\"\n","additions":26,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778689154003,"end":1778689154008}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_018b93804a2968cc016a04a470b1e8819ba84c060e3b9d88d3"}},"id":"prt_e22225896001jhNd1AXJAwU14n","sessionID":"ses_1ddde3f62ffe7ptYFGvwU9A50r","messageID":"msg_e2221f49d0010SCFoZqbR1fW5v"}}
