{"type":"text","timestamp":1778693387654,"sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6cb0ffeTxEWWSpKre73Ol","part":{"id":"prt_e22633160001XmtR9im6XXpc5z","messageID":"msg_e2262cf610018x5LVMiKRwNUT0","sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6cb0ffeTxEWWSpKre73Ol","type":"text","text":"The history shows the strongest surviving micro-opt is keeping the hot RV32I path simple; prior branch/fetch/memory-control additions mostly regressed. I’m writing a narrow M-unit multiplier-sharing hypothesis that preserves current latency/handshake instead of adding new pipeline control.","time":{"start":1778693386592,"end":1778693387652},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0489bf2edb773fff016a04b50a6a548199b2d66e780c56a4fb","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778693403686,"sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6cb0ffeTxEWWSpKre73Ol","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YNZtS7TLOeVRZCl6MzQGYGgF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r8s0\n+title: Share M-unit multiplier hardware\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current best core already removed RV32M arithmetic from the ordinary EX\n+  ALU path, but m_unit still builds three separate 64-bit multiplier products\n+  in parallel for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU signedness variants. CoreMark uses\n+  M operations rarely enough that throughput beyond the existing one-cycle\n+  registered M-unit is not the main limiter, while the extra DSP/LUT/routing\n+  pressure can still depress FPGA Fmax or perturb placement of the hot RV32I\n+  pipeline.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the parallel signed-signed, unsigned-unsigned, and signed-unsigned\n+  product generation in m_unit with one shared signed multiplier fed by\n+  sign/zero-extended operands selected from the M opcode. MUL can take the low\n+  half of the same product because low 32 bits are independent of operand\n+  signedness; MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU select the high half with the appropriate\n+  operand extension. Keep the existing start/valid/clear handshake, one-cycle\n+  M latency, DIV/REM behavior, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions unchanged.\n+  This should trim multiplier area and routing without adding CPI, front-end\n+  prediction logic, memory ordering state, or any RVFI-visible behavior change.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Use a single sign-controlled widened multiplier for MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU while preserving the current M-unit handshake and ALTOPS behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experi