{"type":"text","timestamp":1778695262368,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c37dffeA0edlSklrIPTbJ","part":{"id":"prt_e227fca66001NQ6qCYRPxhVNtS","messageID":"msg_e227f72e0001f2xlH5OTYR1Umy","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c37dffeA0edlSklrIPTbJ","type":"text","text":"Prior micro_opt history points away from adding muxes/control and toward trimming always-carried datapath/control state. The current RTL still carries full decode control through `mem_wb_t` even though WB/RVFI only need `reg_write`, `mem_to_reg`, and `is_illegal`, so I’m writing a narrow-state pruning hypothesis rather than another predictor or stall-hiding change.","time":{"start":1778695260774,"end":1778695262367},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03f07142a68904f4016a04bc5ca7348199ad03452bb549546f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
