{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778697141764,"sessionID":"ses_1dd647d9dffeBsTH93dW9wPxMG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_7xDn8rkN1nJFjfu1bUChGcR3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Handshake IFID register\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end feeds imem_data directly into decode, immediate generation,\n+  regfile read-address selection, load-use hazard checks, and the ID/EX register in\n+  one cycle. Prior structural attempts that added prediction, bypassing, store\n+  buffering, or EX retiming regressed by adding hot mux/control paths. The earlier\n+  IF/ID-register attempt broke because it lacked a real consume/valid handshake,\n+  not because the imem-to-decode retiming target was inherently invalid.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a proper registered IF/ID boundary with an explicit valid bit and ID consume\n+  handshake. IF captures a fetched instruction only when imem is ready and the IF/ID\n+  slot is empty or ID is consuming it; ID consumes exactly one valid entry when the\n+  downstream ID/EX register is not held. Load-use, dmem, and M-unit stalls hold the\n+  IF/ID entry without duplicating it, while EX redirects flush the registered entry\n+  and update PC with redirect priority. This should remove the imem-data-to-decoder\n+  combinational path and improve Fmax, with only a small CPI risk and no change to\n+  the NRET=1 retirement/RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the IF/ID bundle shape but treat it as a registered valid payload with explicit consume semantics documented for the implementation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry registered IF/ID slot with valid, downstream consume, imem-ready capture, and redirect flush/update priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose or honor the ID consume condition so the IF/ID slot advances only when ID/EX captures a new instruction instead of holding or bubbling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF/ID consume signal from existing stall/flush decisions without changing top-level ports or RVFI channel-0 retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Clarify stall versus bubble outputs so load-use bubbles consume the held IF/ID instruction exactly once, while dmem and M-unit holds do not consume it.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Handshake IFID register\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end feeds imem_data directly into decode, immediate generation,\n+  regfile read-address selection, load-use hazard checks, and the ID/EX register in\n+  one cycle. Prior structural attempts that added prediction, bypassing, store\n+  buffering, or EX retiming regressed by adding hot mux/control paths. The earlier\n+  IF/ID-register attempt broke because it lacked a real consume/valid handshake,\n+  not because the imem-to-decode retiming target was inherently invalid.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a proper registered IF/ID boundary with an explicit valid bit and ID consume\n+  handshake. IF captures a fetched instruction only when imem is ready and the IF/ID\n+  slot is empty or ID is consuming it; ID consumes exactly one valid entry when the\n+  downstream ID/EX register is not held. Load-use, dmem, and M-unit stalls hold the\n+  IF/ID entry without duplicating it, while EX redirects flush the registered entry\n+  and update PC with redirect priority. This should remove the imem-data-to-decoder\n+  combinational path and improve Fmax, with only a small CPI risk and no change to\n+  the NRET=1 retirement/RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the IF/ID bundle shape but treat it as a registered valid payload with explicit consume semantics documented for the implementation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry registered IF/ID slot with valid, downstream consume, imem-ready capture, and redirect flush/update priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose or honor the ID consume condition so the IF/ID slot advances only when ID/EX captures a new instruction instead of holding or bubbling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF/ID consume signal from existing stall/flush decisions without changing top-level ports or RVFI channel-0 retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Clarify stall versus bubble outputs so load-use bubbles consume the held IF/ID instruction exactly once, while dmem and M-unit holds do not consume it.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Handshake IFID register\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end feeds imem_data directly into decode, immediate generation,\n+  regfile read-address selection, load-use hazard checks, and the ID/EX register in\n+  one cycle. Prior structural attempts that added prediction, bypassing, store\n+  buffering, or EX retiming regressed by adding hot mux/control paths. The earlier\n+  IF/ID-register attempt broke because it lacked a real consume/valid handshake,\n+  not because the imem-to-decode retiming target was inherently invalid.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a proper registered IF/ID boundary with an explicit valid bit and ID consume\n+  handshake. IF captures a fetched instruction only when imem is ready and the IF/ID\n+  slot is empty or ID is consuming it; ID consumes exactly one valid entry when the\n+  downstream ID/EX register is not held. Load-use, dmem, and M-unit stalls hold the\n+  IF/ID entry without duplicating it, while EX redirects flush the registered entry\n+  and update PC with redirect priority. This should remove the imem-data-to-decoder\n+  combinational path and improve Fmax, with only a small CPI risk and no change to\n+  the NRET=1 retirement/RVFI contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the IF/ID bundle shape but treat it as a registered valid payload with explicit consume semantics documented for the implementation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry registered IF/ID slot with valid, downstream consume, imem-ready capture, and redirect flush/update priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose or honor the ID consume condition so the IF/ID slot advances only when ID/EX captures a new instruction instead of holding or bubbling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF/ID consume signal from existing stall/flush decisions without changing top-level ports or RVFI channel-0 retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Clarify stall versus bubble outputs so load-use bubbles consume the held IF/ID instruction exactly once, while dmem and M-unit holds do not consume it.\"\n","additions":33,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r11s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778697141762,"end":1778697141764}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_063fee3693f1fb47016a04c39f5d0c819b9d5a9d74acd6930c"}},"id":"prt_e229c26e6001nr8qIYs8lhbS6P","sessionID":"ses_1dd647d9dffeBsTH93dW9wPxMG","messageID":"msg_e229c06f80014h0enOQW2L4p2N"}}
