{"type":"text","timestamp":1778697755579,"sessionID":"ses_1dd5aba50ffePoiAC54yOVzkic","part":{"id":"prt_e22a5d3ad001Nk3MeuDUeR278T","messageID":"msg_e22a57f46001mLvOX8Cfwe5Dy0","sessionID":"ses_1dd5aba50ffePoiAC54yOVzkic","type":"text","text":"Structural history is consistent: CPI-oriented structures (predictors, buffers, bypasses, store buffers, deeper EX) mostly regressed or broke; the one successful structural change was removing RVFI-only payload from hot datapath bundles. I’m going to propose the next narrow structural follow-up: split the ID/EX register into hot execution state and an RVFI shadow state, avoiding new prediction or stall machinery.","time":{"start":1778697753517,"end":1778697755578},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0855184a9ce1d6b0016a04c619686c819b861826bf3e7fe7eb","phase":"commentary"}}}}
