RVFI shadow payload, keeping forwarding/source fields needed by EX in the hot payload.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive and register the separate ID/EX execution and RVFI shadow outputs under the existing reset, stall, and flush rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Accept the split ID/EX payloads and use the RVFI shadow only for retirement metadata while preserving existing execute, redirect, and M-unit behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the split ID/EX payloads between decode, execute, hazard, and forwarding without changing the top-level NRET=1 IO contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Split ID/EX RVFI shadow\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only clearly successful structural change in the recent bench history was\n+  splitting RVFI-only metadata away from the hot EX/MEM and MEM/WB datapath\n+  payloads. The current ID/EX register still mixes execution-critical operands,\n+  immediate/control, and forwarding source numbers with RVFI-only instruction\n+  bits and retirement reporting fields. A similarly narrow split at the decode\n+  boundary targets register width, reset/hold muxing, and routing pressure\n+  without adding predictors, memory ordering structures, bypass selects, or an\