{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778698771568,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b95daffeUPuCkcS77kE0Dc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dIDXgoE12c97qVkKPbMf63TH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\n2: title: \"Localize WB-to-ID bypass\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Prior structural attempts show that adding predictors, skid buffers, store buffers,\n6:   load bypasses, or deeper execute retiming usually costs more FPGA fitness than it\n7:   recovers. The remaining promising structural direction is to reduce always-active\n8:   fanout and muxing without changing CPI or control-flow timing. The integer regfile\n9:   currently embeds write-first same-cycle bypass compares and 32-bit muxes on both\n10:   combinational read ports, so WB write-enable/address/data fan out through the\n11:   register file as well as to forwarding, RVFI, and writeback.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Move the same-cycle WB-to-ID bypass out of reg_file and into id_stage as two local\n14:   read-data selects after the raw register-file read. The reg_file would become a\n15:   simpler 2-read/1-write array with x0 forcing only, while id_stage receives the WB\n16:   write port and selects wb_w_data for rs1/rs2 when the decoded source matches the\n17:   retiring destination. This preserves the existing architectural behavior needed\n18:   for consumers that are too far from the writer to be covered by EX forwarding, but\n19:   localizes the write-first muxing near decode and may let synthesis pack the regfile\n20:   array and WB fanout better. It avoids changing pipeline depth, redirect timing,\n21:   memory ordering, RVFI retirement, or the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n22: expected_impact:\n23:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n24:   confidence: medium\n25: changes:\n26:   - file: rtl/reg_file.sv\n27:     description: \"Remove embedded same-cycle write-first bypass muxes from the combinational read ports, keeping x0 forcing and the synchronous write behavior.\"\n28:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n29:     description: \"Accept the WB write-enable/address/data signals and apply local rs1/rs2 bypass selection before filling the ID/EX register.\"\n30:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n31:     description: \"Wire the existing WB write port signals into id_stage while preserving the current NRET=1 RVFI port set and pipeline control.\"\n\n(End of file - total 31 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\ntitle: \"Localize WB-to-ID bypass\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  Prior structural attempts show that adding predictors, skid buffers, store buffers,\n  load bypasses, or deeper execute retiming usually costs more FPGA fitness than it\n  recovers. The remaining promising structural direction is to reduce always-active\n  fanout and muxing without changing CPI or control-flow timing. The integer regfile\n  currently embeds write-first same-cycle bypass compares and 32-bit muxes on both\n  combinational read ports, so WB write-enable/address/data fan out through the\n  register file as well as to forwarding, RVFI, and writeback.\nhypothesis: |\n  Move the same-cycle WB-to-ID bypass out of reg_file and into id_stage as two local\n  read-data selects after the raw register-file read. The reg_file would become a\n  simpler 2-read/1-write array with x0 forcing only, while id_stage receives the WB\n  write port and selects wb_w_data for rs1/rs2 when the decoded source matches the\n  retiring destination. This preserves the existing architectural behavior needed\n  for consumers that are too far from the writer to be covered by EX forwarding, but\n  localizes the write-first muxing near decode and may let synthesis pack the regfile\n  array and WB fanout better. It avoids changing pipeline depth, redirect timing,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778698771565,"end":1778698771567}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0eb9e04c2e3c4deb016a04ca12da50819bb8378ec121fada9f"}},"id":"prt_e22b55a15001beJ20tgxJ546bw","sessionID":"ses_1dd4b95daffeUPuCkcS77kE0Dc","messageID":"msg_e22b5451b001vtwM8XZBVB3H41"}}
