{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778700535308,"sessionID":"ses_1dd3084bbffewQR02X96tDltPk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ahDOt3vSKH0AzFj4GQh3ispe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retire-only RVFI memory shadow\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only clearly successful structural direction for the current bench core was\n+  splitting RVFI-only metadata away from hot execution payloads. A later MEM-side\n+  split regressed because it duplicated byte-mask and write-data work around the\n+  load/writeback path, but the current MEM stage still clocks RVFI-only memory\n+  sideband fields under the same always-active MEM/WB register block as the hot\n+  execution result. A narrower retire-only shadow can reduce enable/reset routing\n+  and payload fanout without adding CPI, prediction, bypass selects, or memory\n+  ordering state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing EX/MEM execution and RVFI shadow inputs unchanged, but split\n+  the MEM/WB RVFI memory sideband register into a separate retire-only module or\n+  local register block that is updated from already-computed MEM-stage signals.\n+  The hot MEM/WB execution register should retain only alu_result, load_data, rd,\n+  ctrl, and valid, while the RVFI memory/PC/source/instruction fields follow the\n+  same hold_wb, reset, misalignment, and valid decisions in a parallel shadow path.\n+  Unlike the failed broader MEM split, do not recompute masks, replicated store\n+  data, or load extraction in two places; share the existing combinational results\n+  and only separate the sequential payload and assignment fanout. This should trim\n+  routing around the MEM retirement boundary while preserving the NRET=1 port\n+  contract, RVFI aligned-memory reporting, trap behavior, and CoreMark timing\n+  markers.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Introduce or document a separate retire-only MEM/WB RVFI shadow payload while keeping the execution payload shape stable.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Separate the MEM/WB execution register from the RVFI memory/PC/source shadow register, sharing existing computed mask/data signals and preserving hold_wb behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the separated MEM/WB RVFI shadow outputs to the existing single-channel RVFI port assignments without changing the NRET=1 top-level interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Retire-only RVFI memory shadow\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The only clearly successful structural direction for the current bench core was\n+  splitting RVFI-only metadata away from hot execution payloads. A later MEM-side\n+  split regressed because it duplicated byte-mask and write-data work around the\n+  load/writeback path, but the current MEM stage still clocks RVFI-only memory\n+  sideband fields under the same always-active MEM/WB register block as the hot\n+  execution result. A narrower retire-only shadow can reduce enable/reset routing\n+  and payload fanout without adding CPI, prediction, bypass