{"type":"text","timestamp":1778677742737,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c3237ffe0PhGxV9Vz6Pfwk","part":{"id":"prt_e21747c2d001Zgp9u767IGkoQ6","messageID":"msg_e21743b37001yOR50cXoScCdql","sessionID":"ses_1de8c3237ffe0PhGxV9Vz6Pfwk","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis file now. The proposal is intentionally one structural angle: move control-flow resolution one stage earlier to reduce taken branch/jump bubbles in CoreMark loops.","time":{"start":1778677742637,"end":1778677742735},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_01856b89f0d85404016a0477ee8748819a954efa5af6f43028","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778677761047,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c3237ffe0PhGxV9Vz6Pfwk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Cdcsgqst2Yn2t0l9mj5P9Ws7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Resolve control flow in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark spends a significant fraction of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common taken-control penalty from two bubbles to one while preserving RVFI order, trap reporting, and single-channel retirement.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage early redirect signals into the IF and hazard path while preserving the existing NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add early branch/JAL/JALR resolution using decoded control, immediates, regfile operands, and forwarded compare/base operands.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Extend forwarding selection to provide decode-stage operands for early branch compares and JALR target calculation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust control-hazard flushing and load-use detection so early ID redirects flush only the younger fetched instruction and stall when a branch operand is waiting on a load.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove EX-owned redirect as the primary PC control source while keeping misalignment trap metadata and resolved pc_next consistent for RVFI.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Resolve control flow in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  CoreMark spends a significant fraction of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common taken-control penalty from two bubbles to one while preserving RVFI order, trap reporting, and single-channel retirement.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage early redirect signals into the IF and hazard path while preserving the existing NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add early branch/JAL/JALR resolution using decoded control, immediates, regfile operands, and forwarded compare/base operands.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Extend forwarding selection to provide decode-stage operands for early branch compares and JALR target calculation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust control-hazard flushing and load-use detection so early ID redirects flush only the younger fetched instruction and stall when a branch operand is waiting on a load.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove EX-owned redirect as the primary PC control source while keeping misalignment trap metadata and resolved pc_next consistent for RVFI.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id