{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778677777748,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c3237ffe0PhGxV9Vz6Pfwk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_r8YaP5iz7rC3W0NrmVLKM0Up","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\n2: title: \"Resolve control flow in ID\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   CoreMark spends a significant fraction of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\n6: hypothesis: |\n7:   Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common taken-control penalty from two bubbles to one while preserving RVFI order, trap reporting, and single-channel retirement.\n8: expected_impact:\n9:   fitness_delta_pct: 8\n10:   confidence: medium\n11: changes:\n12:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n13:     description: \"Wire ID-stage early redirect signals into the IF and hazard path while preserving the existing NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n14:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n15:     description: \"Add early branch/JAL/JALR resolution using decoded control, immediates, regfile operands, and forwarded compare/base operands.\"\n16:   - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n17:     description: \"Extend forwarding selection to provide decode-stage operands for early branch compares and JALR target calculation.\"\n18:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n19:     description: \"Adjust control-hazard flushing and load-use detection so early ID redirects flush only the younger fetched instruction and stall when a branch operand is waiting on a load.\"\n20:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n21:     description: \"Remove EX-owned redirect as the primary PC control source while keeping misalignment trap metadata and resolved pc_next consistent for RVFI.\"\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\ntitle: \"Resolve control flow in ID\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  CoreMark spends a significant fraction of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\nhypothesis: |\n  Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common taken-control penalty from two bubbles to one while preserving RVFI order, trap reporting, and single-channel retirement.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire ID-stage early redirect signals into the IF and hazard path while preserving the existing NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n    description: \"Add early branch/JAL/JALR resolution using decoded control, immediates, regfile operands, and forwarded compare/base operands.\"\n  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n    description: \"Extend forwarding selection to provide decode-stage operands for early branch compares and JALR target calculation.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Adjust control-hazard flushing and load-use detection so early ID redirects flush only the younger fetched instruction and stall when a branch operand is waiting on a load.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r1s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778677777733,"end":1778677777747}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0de30045de534897016a04780ed9c0819b83820e7fee37a18b"}},"id":"prt_e2174fc85001FDoB0Ie0S95erv","sessionID":"ses_1de8c3237ffe0PhGxV9Vz6Pfwk","messageID":"msg_e2174c490002tJwXoReizb0xbc"}}
