m stalls, hold the outstanding fetch instead of emitting a synthetic NOP into decode. This should overlap random iStall cycles with existing back-end stalls and reduce front-end bubbles while preserving single-retire RVFI ordering and the existing EX-stage control-flow correctness.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 7\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n    description: \"Adjust IF-to-ID bundle comments/types if needed so the payload represents a buffered valid instruction rather than a purely combinational fetch result.\"\n  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n    description: \"Replace the combinational IF/ID output with a small valid-ready fetch skid buffer that tracks outstanding sequential fetches, flushes on redirect, and only presents valid instructions to decode when available.\"\n  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n    description: \"Separate front-end fetch backpressure from decode stalls so imem stalls do not force decode bubbles when a buffered instruction is available, while redirects and back-end holds still have priority.\"\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: \"Wire the fetch-buffer availability/consume signals between IF, ID, and hazard logic without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO or RVFI channel-0 retirement contract.\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r2s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778679001836,"end":1778679001839}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09f94daae040258b016a047cd8ec4c8198938842296fc00c53"}},"id":"prt_e2187afcd001Xoo4GcGMMBttF6","sessionID":"ses_1de7941beffepjxUFM8Diz3UWE","messageID":"msg_e21879c2c001z6lzBTZR13SAgJ"}}
