{"type":"text","timestamp":1778680485320,"sessionID":"ses_1de624a85ffeQqxJYJoyypoNcW","part":{"id":"prt_e219e551000194p3v5w61U88N9","messageID":"msg_e219de9810021OypFvoUDlMtoU","sessionID":"ses_1de624a85ffeQqxJYJoyypoNcW","type":"text","text":"The log shows both previous structural attempts targeted control/front-end bubbles and failed or regressed. A better structural slot is the remaining textbook pipeline interlock: remove the one-cycle load-use bubble by adding a MEM-stage load-data bypass into EX, which improves CoreMark CPI without fetch-path prediction logic.","time":{"start":1778680485136,"end":1778680485319},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_091820542c44e9c2016a0482a501cc819a88cd07bb9bd198fc","phase":"commentary"}}}}
