{"type":"text","timestamp":1778682585988,"sessionID":"ses_1de422f65ffellC52CFAtcGJ1y","part":{"id":"prt_e21be60a1001PSrg6uyxBtVZTx","messageID":"msg_e21be0a53001RUzvHjsyWIh0dr","sessionID":"ses_1de422f65ffellC52CFAtcGJ1y","type":"text","text":"The prior structural attempts mainly spent timing on front-end buffering/control prediction or load bypassing and regressed. The cleaner structural angle is to add a real IF/ID register to cut the fetch-memory-to-decode path, accepting a small CPI cost for a likely Fmax gain instead of adding more bypass or predictor muxing.","time":{"start":1778682585249,"end":1778682585986},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_062c536b8c71a1b6016a048ad91dd4819a82f50d70d529d679","phase":"commentary"}}}}
