{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778682615237,"sessionID":"ses_1de422f65ffellC52CFAtcGJ1y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_XVpX2odgM7Mqmlst8ifKWrd8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register IF/ID fetch boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end feeds imem_data directly through decode, immediate\n+  generation, regfile address decode, hazard checks, and into the ID/EX\n+  register in a single cycle. Prior structural attempts tried to hide stalls or\n+  reduce bubbles with added prediction and bypass control, but those changes\n+  regressed by lengthening already sensitive mux/control paths. A real IF/ID\n+  register is a simpler structural retiming that targets Fmax directly.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Insert a proper IF/ID pipeline register inside the fetch stage, so fetched\n+  instruction, PC, and valid are captured before decode sees them. The PC still\n+  advances only when the downstream ID stage can accept the entry, and redirect\n+  flushes the registered IF/ID payload before wrong-path state can retire. This\n+  adds one front-end cycle and may slightly increase taken-control penalty, but\n+  it removes the imem-to-decoder combinational path and should improve FPGA\n+  Fmax enough to raise CoreMark iter/sec without changing the NRET=1 retirement\n+  contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing IF/ID bundle shape, but document and use it as a registered pipeline boundary rather than a combinational fetch payload.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an IF/ID register for pc, instruction, and valid; hold it on decode stalls, clear it on reset/redirect/flush, and preserve redirect priority over ordinary stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust stall and flush semantics for the registered IF/ID boundary so imem stalls hold fetch state instead of injecting decode NOPs, while load-use and redirect bubbles remain correct.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the unchanged IF/ID bundle through the new registered fetch boundary and keep the single-channel RVFI retirement interface unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Register IF/ID fetch boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current front end feeds imem_data directly through decode, immediate\n+  generation, regfile address decode, hazard checks, and into the ID/EX\n+  register in a single cycle. Prior structural attempts tried to hide stalls or\n+  reduce bubbles with added prediction and bypass control, but those changes\n+  regressed by lengthening already sensitive mux/control paths. A real IF/ID\n+  register is a simpler structural retiming that targets Fmax directly.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Insert a proper IF/ID pipeline register inside the fetch stage, so fetched\n+  instruction, PC, and valid are captured before decode sees them. The PC still\n+  advances only when the downstream ID stage can accept the entry, and redirect\n+  flushes the registered IF/ID payload before wrong-path state can retire. This\n+  adds one front-end cycle and may slightly increase taken-control penalty, but\n+  it removes the imem-to-decoder combinational path and should improve FPGA\n+  Fmax enough to raise CoreMark iter/sec without changing the NRET=1 retirement\n+  contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the existing IF/ID bundle shape, but document and use it as a registered pipeline boundary rather than a combinational fetch payload.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an IF/ID register for pc, instruction, and valid; hold it on decode stalls, clear it on reset/redirect/flush, and preserve redirect priority over ordinary stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Adjust stall and flush semantics for the registered IF/ID boundary so imem stalls hold fetch state instead of injecting decode NOPs, while load-use and redirect bubbles remain correct.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the unchanged IF/ID bundle through the new registered fetch boundary and keep the single-channel RVFI retirement interface unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/ben