{"type":"text","timestamp":1778684891874,"sessionID":"ses_1de1f19aaffeftqYOGcZLT0vo0","part":{"id":"prt_e21e18db0001nvMOsMsbGryOj2","messageID":"msg_e21e119eb001edq1PmO06Lm2nY","sessionID":"ses_1de1f19aaffeftqYOGcZLT0vo0","type":"text","text":"The structural history shows front-end buffering, IF/ID retiming, and MEM-load bypass have already regressed or broken. I’m choosing a different structural angle: a tightly ordered one-entry store buffer that targets random dmem store stalls without adding fetch-path prediction or load-data bypass muxes.","time":{"start":1778684890544,"end":1778684891870},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02a47d115c501ec5016a0493da6890819889e799e3ec4e3b45","phase":"commentary"}}}}
