{"type":"text","timestamp":1778687332463,"sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c25cffezPuCxxaEhdOvsr","part":{"id":"prt_e2206cb27001Ypzb9x0iSCMPnp","messageID":"msg_e2206731e001XaBBNGn8VbB93G","sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c25cffezPuCxxaEhdOvsr","type":"text","text":"The relevant structural history is mostly negative: front-end buffering/prediction, early branch resolution, load bypass, and store buffering all lost or broke due to added control-path cost. The hypothesis I’m writing targets structural retiming instead: adding a narrow register boundary inside EX to cut the forwarding/ALU/branch/MEM-register cone, accepting a small CPI cost only if Fmax gain is enough.","time":{"start":1778687331111,"end":1778687332459},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d35601babcb72bc016a049d62ff18819b92057a38820f6b76","phase":"commentary"}}}}
