{"type":"text","timestamp":1778689132186,"sessionID":"ses_1ddde3ef1ffelGBZQCOkrNjfqc","part":{"id":"prt_e22223ff0001HgQG7i3KpnTsYn","messageID":"msg_e2221ef06001onopzY80dIzd6j","sessionID":"ses_1ddde3ef1ffelGBZQCOkrNjfqc","type":"text","text":"The structural history is mostly negative for front-end buffers, early branch resolution, load bypass, store buffering, and EX splitting. I’m choosing a narrower structural retiming hypothesis that targets dmem-ready/control fanout without adding prediction, bypass selects, or new ordering machinery.","time":{"start":1778689130480,"end":1778689132184},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04b887a54eff3a8f016a04a46a59a4819994897f1a9740e1ca","phase":"commentary"}}}}
