{"type":"text","timestamp":1778693373510,"sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6dacffeihw7ZVTZ2qaxYo","part":{"id":"prt_e2262f8a0001kbgDwVxnljXKCf","messageID":"msg_e2262bcb8001QJBA25kcp1s0uE","sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6dacffeihw7ZVTZ2qaxYo","type":"text","text":"The prior structural attempts mostly regressed by adding front-end predictors/buffers, memory overlap machinery, or deeper EX latency. I’m choosing a lower-risk structural retiming: register the WB result at the MEM/WB boundary so forwarding/regfile/RVFI no longer depend on a post-MEM/WB writeback mux.","time":{"start":1778693372064,"end":1778693373507},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0dff51a211d6d154016a04b4fbf18c819998f72b831d898ffe","phase":"commentary"}}}}
