{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778693403860,"sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6dacffeihw7ZVTZ2qaxYo","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_96cKukke8T500vtGdzhZ4WHS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Register WB result at MEM boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The recent structural attempts mostly lost fitness by adding control-flow\n+  prediction, buffering, memory overlap, or deeper execute-stage interlocks.\n+  A safer structural target is the existing MEM/WB-to-WB combinational path:\n+  the selected writeback value is still muxed after the MEM/WB register, then\n+  fans out to the regfile write port, same-cycle regfile bypass, EX forwarding,\n+  and RVFI rd_wdata. Registering that selected value at the retirement boundary\n+  should shorten a hot fanout path without changing CPI, branch timing, memory\n+  ordering, or the NRET=1 external contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a preselected rd_wdata/writeback-result field to the MEM/WB pipeline\n+  bundle and compute it inside mem_stage before the MEM/WB register captures.\n+  For loads this field captures the sign/zero-extended load result; for ALU,\n+  JAL, JALR, AUIPC, LUI, and M-extension operations it captures the existing\n+  EX/MEM alu_result. Then simplify wb_stage into a pass-through of the\n+  registered writeback value instead of a post-register mem_to_reg mux. This\n+  structural retiming preserves the same retirement boundary and RVFI data, but\n+  removes the load-vs-ALU mux from the next cycle's forwarding/regfile/RVFI\n+  fanout cone, which may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax with essentially no\n+  iterations-per-cycle penalty.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a registered writeback-result field to mem_wb_t so the MEM/WB boundary carries the already-selected rd data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and capture the selected writeback result alongside existing MEM/WB fields, retaining hold_wb behavior for forwarding during dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the post-MEM/WB mem_to_reg mux with a pass-through of the registered writeback result while preserving write enable and x0 handling.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Register WB result at MEM boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The recent structural attempts mostly lost fitness by adding control-flow\n+  prediction, buffering, memory overlap, or deeper execute-stage interlocks.\n+  A safer structural target is the existing MEM/WB-to-WB combinational path:\n+  the selected writeback value is still muxed after the MEM/WB register, then\n+  fans out to the regfile write port, same-cycle regfile bypass, EX forwarding,\n+  and RVFI rd_wdata. Registering that selected value at the retirement boundary\n+  should shorten a hot fanout path without changing CPI, branch timing, memory\n+  ordering, or the NRET=1 external contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a preselected rd_wdata/writeback-result field to the MEM/WB pipeline\n+  bundle and compute it inside mem_stage before the MEM/WB register captures.\n+  For loads this field captures the sign/zero-extended load result; for ALU,\n+  JAL, JALR, AUIPC, LUI, and M-extension operations it captures the existing\n+  EX/MEM alu_result. Then simplify wb_stage into a pass-through of the\n+  registered writeback value instead of a post-register mem_to_reg mux. This\n+  structural retiming preserves the same retirement boundary and RVFI data, but\n+  removes the load-vs-ALU mux from the next cycle's forwarding/regfile/RVFI\n+  fanout cone, which may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax with essentially no\n+  iterations-per-cycle penalty.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a registered writeback-result field to mem_wb_t so the MEM/WB boundary carries the already-selected rd data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and capture the selected writeback result alongside existing MEM/WB fields, retaining hold_wb behavior for forwarding during dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the post-MEM/WB mem_to_reg mux with a pass-through of the registered writeback result while preserving write enable and x0 handling.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.c