{"type":"text","timestamp":1778695252624,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c300ffegtSktSydTtYrF4","part":{"id":"prt_e227fa0cc001jG6DenVnYHopPG","messageID":"msg_e227f6f5f001kZ1Hqntye1o1Kp","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c300ffegtSktSydTtYrF4","type":"text","text":"Prior structural attempts consistently regressed when they added prediction, buffering, memory overlap, or deeper execution interlocks. The least-overlapping structural angle is to reduce the width and fanout of hot pipeline registers by separating execution payload from RVFI shadow metadata, preserving behavior while targeting FPGA packing/routing rather than CPI.","time":{"start":1778695250124,"end":1778695252623},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08ce831af80c193f016a04bc5206cc8198a9c5aaef01053c85","phase":"commentary"}}}}
