{"type":"text","timestamp":1778695262638,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c300ffegtSktSydTtYrF4","part":{"id":"prt_e227fd091001IG3gMiFISmNx9k","messageID":"msg_e227fb2b8001QeOV8qxyMJO2g4","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c300ffegtSktSydTtYrF4","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis YAML now, scoped only to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/` and using short `rtl/...` change paths.","time":{"start":1778695262353,"end":1778695262637},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0de11dee656a52f9016a04bc5e3ae481999951ecc40586d427","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778695282091,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c300ffegtSktSydTtYrF4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_l7S8dF3tWoVGSFc5ngfMkwei","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: Split RVFI shadow metadata from datapath\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best recent gains came from removing broad arithmetic and register fanout from hot paths, while most structural attempts regressed by adding prediction, buffering, memory overlap, or extra execute-stage interlocks. The current pipeline still carries a wide all-purpose struct through EX/MEM and MEM/WB, mixing hot execution data with RVFI-only metadata such as original source values, source register numbers, instruction bits, memory masks, and retired PC fields. Even when those fields are not part of the architectural datapath, they share the same pipeline registers, reset/hold enables, and module boundaries as timing-critical forwarding, memory, and writeback signals.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the pipeline state into a narrow execution payload and a parallel RVFI shadow payload. Keep the hot EX/MEM and MEM/WB datapath bundles limited to control bits and values needed for forwarding, dmem, writeback, and stalls, while carrying RVFI-only fields in a separate shadow register chain that uses the same valid, flush, hold, trap, and redirect decisions. This should reduce register width, enable fanout, and routing pressure on the timing-critical datapath without changing CPI, branch resolution timing, memory ordering, RVFI contents, or the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Define narrower execution pipeline bundles plus a separate RVFI shadow bundle for fields only used at retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Populate narrow EX/MEM datapath state and advance matching RVFI shadow metadata under the existing stall and M-unit rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep memory and writeback datapath state narrow while updating RVFI shadow memory fields, traps, masks, and valid state in lockstep.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the separated datapath and RVFI shadow outputs to the existing hazard, forwarding, writeback, and single-channel RVFI ports.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r9s1\n+title: Split RVFI shadow metadata from datapath\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best recent gains came from removing broad arithmetic and register fanout from hot paths, while most structural attempts regressed by adding prediction, buffering, memory overlap, or extra execute-stage interlocks. The current pipeline still carries a wide all-purpose struct through EX/MEM and MEM/WB, mixing hot execution data with RVFI-only metadata such as original source values, source register numbers, instruction bits, memory masks, and retired PC fields. Even when those fields are not part of the architectural datapath, they share the same pipeline registers, reset/hold enables, and module boundaries as timing-critical forwarding, memory, and writeback signals.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the pipeline state into a narrow execution payload and a parallel RVFI shadow payload. Keep the hot EX/MEM and MEM/WB datapath bundles limited to control bits and values needed for forwarding, dmem, writeback, and stalls, while carrying RVFI-only fields in a separate shadow register chain that uses the same valid, flush, hold, trap, and redirect decisions. This should reduce register width, enable fanout, and routing pressure on the timing-critical datapath without changing CPI, branch resolution timing, memory ordering, RVFI contents, or the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Define narrower execution pipeline bundles plus a separate RVFI shadow bundle for fields only used at retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Populate narrow EX/MEM datapath state and advance matching RVFI shadow metadata under the existing stall and M-unit rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep memory and writeback datapath state narrow while updating RVFI shadow memory fields, traps, masks, and valid state in lockstep.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the separated datapath and RVFI shadow outputs to the existing hazard, forwarding, writeback, and single-channel RVFI ports.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260