{"type":"text","timestamp":1778696154575,"sessionID":"ses_1dd72e66fffeV0N6pEVOq8AGwG","part":{"id":"prt_e228d6444002Xzr9DUnLVl4p7s","messageID":"msg_e228d4765001rNRTv9eJl1axDZ","sessionID":"ses_1dd72e66fffeV0N6pEVOq8AGwG","type":"text","text":"The predictor history is consistently negative when adding IF/ID target logic or metadata. I’m choosing a deliberately narrower predictor: an EX-trained single-entry “next-line after taken branch” suppressor that avoids fetch target arithmetic and only learns one hot loop branch, with low confidence and modest expected impact.","time":{"start":1778696152132,"end":1778696154574},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b4c216ef958c29f016a04bfd806fc819b9d4e6836c4c2b34b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778696175686,"sessionID":"ses_1dd72e66fffeV0N6pEVOq8AGwG","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_tgeBsBOxPTbymQ9YyYf20YfH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Single hot loop branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added immediate\n+  decode, target adders, return-stack state, counters, or multi-entry tag logic\n+  to the fetch/decode control paths. CoreMark still spends cycles on repeated\n+  taken loop-closing branches, but the predictor must be smaller than the prior\n+  BTB, RAS, JAL, and decode-backward experiments to have any chance of paying\n+  on Tang Nano 20K fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add the smallest possible EX-trained predictor for one hot taken conditional\n+  branch: store a single branch PC and its already-resolved target when EX sees\n+  a taken backward branch, predict that target only on an exact PC match, and\n+  invalidate the entry when the same branch later resolves not-taken. Unlike the\n+  failed BTFNT and BTB attempts, IF performs no instruction immediate decode and\n+  no target addition; it only compares the current PC with one registered PC and\n+  muxes between pc+4 and one registered target. Carry a one-bit predicted flag\n+  and predicted next PC to EX so correct predictions suppress the normal taken\n+  redirect while mismatches use the existing recovery path. This targets the most\n+  common loop bubble with minimal predictor state and avoids JAL/JALR/RAS logic.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX-stage prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add one EX-trained branch-PC/target entry, exact-PC hit detection, pc+4-or-target next-PC selection, and invalidation on loop exit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved conditional-branch next PC against the carried prediction, suppress redirects on correct predictions, and emit predictor update signals for taken backward branches and not-taken exits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor metadata and EX update signals between IF and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r10s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Single hot loop branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added immediate\n+  decode, target adders, return-stack state, counters, or multi-entry tag logic\n+  to the fetch/decode control paths. CoreMark still spends cycles on repeated\n+  taken loop-closing branches, but the predictor must be smaller than the prior\n+  BTB, RAS, JAL, and decode-backward experiments to have any chance of paying\n+  on Tang Nano 20K fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add the smallest possible EX-trained predictor for one hot taken conditional\n+  branch: store a single branch PC and its already-resolved target when EX sees\n+  a taken backward br