{"type":"text","timestamp":1778697103504,"sessionID":"ses_1dd647e81ffeaJ9isAlwiYFZg5","part":{"id":"prt_e229be060002rUaXMlgAnIN7rd","messageID":"msg_e229bad4f001588dRdXZ5KRDIO","sessionID":"ses_1dd647e81ffeaJ9isAlwiYFZg5","type":"text","text":"The predictor history is consistently negative when prediction adds IF/decode target logic or predicted-PC metadata. I’m going to propose a deliberately minimal predictor angle: reuse the existing sequential not-taken prediction, but add a no-new-state redirect-elision path for architecturally taken control transfers whose resolved target is already the fall-through PC, avoiding unnecessary flushes without adding fetch-side predictors.","time":{"start":1778697101408,"end":1778697103503},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02fd0bebf7b69a61016a04c38d4e00819899c8f13efae27339","phase":"commentary"}}}}
