{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778697125228,"sessionID":"ses_1dd647e81ffeaJ9isAlwiYFZg5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YQDlD7d0WfpjDUl3bCga3eVK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Fall-through redirect elision\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior predictor that added fetch-side target arithmetic, tags, counters,\n+  return-stack state, or predicted-PC metadata has regressed or broken this core.\n+  The current front end is already a static not-taken predictor for conditional\n+  branches, but EX still treats any resolved taken branch or jump as a redirect\n+  and flushes younger stages even when the resolved target equals the fall-through\n+  PC that fetch already predicted. Avoiding those false redirects is a predictor\n+  refinement with almost no new state or fetch-path cost.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  In EX, compute the sequential fall-through PC as pc+4 and suppress redirect\n+  when the resolved branch or jump target equals that fall-through address. The\n+  instruction should still retire with rvfi_pc_wdata equal to the architecturally\n+  resolved target, but the front end does not need to flush because it has already\n+  fetched the correct next instruction under the existing not-taken prediction.\n+  This keeps all prediction logic out of IF and avoids carrying predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata, while recovering bubbles from short JALs, degenerate branches, and\n+  any compiler-generated control transfers whose target is the next instruction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress redirect when the resolved branch or jump target is exactly pc+4, while preserving pc_next and misalignment-trap behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Fall-through redirect elision\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior predictor that added fetch-side target arithmetic, tags, counters,\n+  return-stack state, or predicted-PC metadata has regressed or broken this core.\n+  The current front end is already a static not-taken predictor for conditional\n+  branches, but EX still treats any resolved taken branch or jump as a redirect\n+  and flushes younger stages even when the resolved target equals the fall-through\n+  PC that fetch already predicted. Avoiding those false redirects is a predictor\n+  refinement with almost no new state or fetch-path cost.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  In EX, compute the sequential fall-through PC as pc+4 and suppress redirect\n+  when the resolved branch or jump target equals that fall-through address. The\n+  instruction should still retire with rvfi_pc_wdata equal to the architecturally\n+  resolved target, but the front end does not need to flush because it has already\n+  fetched the correct next instruction under the existing not-taken prediction.\n+  This keeps all prediction logic out of IF and avoids carrying predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata, while recovering bubbles from short JALs, degenerate branches, and\n+  any compiler-generated control transfers whose target is the next instruction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress redirect when the resolved branch or jump target is exactly pc+4, while preserving pc_next and misalignment-trap behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r11s2\n+title: \"Fall-through redirect elision\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Every prior predictor that added fetch-side target arithmetic, tags, counters,\n+  return-stack state, or predicted-PC metadata has regressed or broken this core.\n+  The current front end is already a static not-taken predictor for conditional\n+  branches, but EX still treats any resolved taken branch or jump as a redirect\n+  and flushes younger stages even when the resolved target equals the fall-through\n+  PC that fetch already predicted. Avoiding those false redirects is a predictor\n+  refinement with almost no new state or fetch-path cost.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  In EX, compute the sequential fall-through PC as pc+4 and suppress redirect\n+  when the resolved branch or jump target equals that fall-through address. The\n+  instruction should still retire with rvfi_pc_wdata equal to the architecturally\n+  resolved target, but the front end does not need to flush because it has already\n+  fetched the correct next instruction under the existing not-taken prediction.\n+  This keeps all prediction logic out of IF and avoids carrying predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata, while recovering bubbles from short JALs, degenerate branches, and\n+  any compiler-generated control transfers whose target is the next instruction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress redirect when the resolved branch or jump target is exactly pc+4, while preserving pc_next and misalignment-trap behavior.\"\n","additions":26,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r11s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778697125225,"end":1778697125227}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c69a8b36ec43581016a04c395670c81999ec3e13829bd6452"}},"id":"prt_e229c0004001DW3BHzKg7H3eEM","sessionID":"ses_1dd647e81ffeaJ9isAlwiYFZg5","messageID":"msg_e229bf1550016GHnTjHSztmsj2"}}
