{"type":"text","timestamp":1778697744892,"sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","part":{"id":"prt_e22a5adf80015fGObybwKTvrSc","messageID":"msg_e22a579d1001VR2e0En12B7C5c","sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","type":"text","text":"The history shows every stateful or early-target predictor has lost fitness, mostly from IF/decode timing and predicted-PC metadata. I’m writing a deliberately conservative predictor hypothesis: treat the current sequential fetch as the predictor and only add a tiny EX-stage “taken target equals already-fetched sequential PC” bypass if implemented with no fetch-path state, but with low confidence because the closest prior attempt regressed.","time":{"start":1778697743865,"end":1778697744890},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07159a36ab7382f5016a04c60faed081998fc249a8aa6dc049","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778697769963,"sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_HZqrBEcmSSPAzsdsr7niPm4v","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: Minimal not-taken predictor cleanup\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core have consistently regressed or broken\n+  because target adders, tags, counters, RAS state, or predicted-PC metadata\n+  lengthened hot fetch/decode/control paths. The only predictor already present\n+  and essentially free is static sequential fetch: conditional branches are\n+  predicted not taken by default. The remaining predictor opportunity should\n+  therefore avoid any IF-side target computation or learned state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Reframe the front end as an explicit static not-taken predictor and make the\n+  smallest possible EX-side cleanup around it: for resolved control transfers,\n+  suppress the pipeline flush only when the resolved next PC is exactly the\n+  sequential pc+4 that the existing fetch path already predicted. Do not add a\n+  BTB, RAS, counters, branch immediate decode in IF, or predicted-PC fields in\n+  pipeline bundles. If implemented narrowly in ex_stage, this can recover rare\n+  false redirect bubbles without perturbing the fetch path or RVFI retirement;\n+  if the needed comparator sits on the branch critical path, it should be\n+  abandoned quickly because the prior broader fall-through-elision attempt\n+  regressed.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate redirect with a resolved-target-versus-pc-plus-four check so the existing static not-taken prediction is not flushed when it was already correct.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: Minimal not-taken predictor cleanup\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core have consistently regressed or broken\n+  because target adders, tags, counters, RAS state, or predicted-PC metadata\n+  lengthened hot fetch/decode/control paths. The only predictor already present\n+  and essentially free is static sequential fetch: conditional branches are\n+  predicted not taken by default. The remaining predictor opportunity should\n+  therefore avoid any IF-side target computation or learned state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Reframe the front end as an explicit static not-taken predictor and make the\n+  smallest possible EX-side cleanup around it: for resolved control transfers,\n+  suppress the pipeline flush only when the resolved next PC is exactly the\n+  sequential pc+4 that the existing fetch path already predicted. Do not add a\n+  BTB, RAS, counters, branch immediate decode in IF, or predicted-PC fields in\n+  pipeline bundles. If implemented narrowly in ex_stage, this can recover rare\n+  false redirect bubbles without perturbing the fetch path or RVFI retirement;\n+  if the needed comparator sits on the branch critical path, it should be\n+  abandoned quickly because the prior broader fall-through-elision attempt\n+  regressed.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate redirect with a resolved-target-versus-pc-plus-four check so the existing static not-taken prediction is not flushed when it was already correct.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: Minimal not-taken predictor cleanup\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core have consistently regressed or broken\n+  because target adders, tags, counters, RAS state, or predicted-PC metadata\n+  lengthened hot fetch/decode/control paths. The only predictor already present\n+  and essentially free is static sequential fetch: conditional branches are\n+  predicted not taken by default. The remaining predictor opportunity should\n+  therefore avoid any IF-side target computation or learned state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Reframe the front end as an explicit static not-taken predictor and make the\n+  smallest possible EX-side cleanup around it: for resolved control transfers,\n+  suppress the pipeline flush only when the resolved next PC is exactly the\n+  sequential pc+4 that the existing fetch path already predicted. Do not add a\n+  BTB, RAS, counters, branch immediate decode in IF, or predicted-PC fields in\n+  pipeline bundles. If implemented narrowly in ex_stage, this can recover rare\n+  false redirect bubbles without perturbing the fetch path or RVFI retirement;\n+  if the needed comparator sits on the branch critical path, it should be\n+  abandoned quickly because the prior broader fall-through-elision attempt\n+  regressed.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate redirect with a resolved-target-versus-pc-plus-four check so the existing static not-taken prediction is not flushed when it was already correct.\"\n","additions":27,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778697769958,"end":1778697769962}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07159a36ab7382f5016a04c610c4d48199ade21bf80bf81bc4"}},"id":"prt_e22a5b1fc001PGL39lfkJ90De6","sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","messageID":"msg_e22a579d1001VR2e0En12B7C5c"}}
