{"type":"text","timestamp":1778697804787,"sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","part":{"id":"prt_e22a696d7001czhP59KfosSqOK","messageID":"msg_e22a61495001BhbflNDJ1oAXym","sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","type":"text","text":"The first draft overlapped too closely with the immediately regressed fall-through attempt. I’m replacing it with a guarded retry of the broken single-hot-loop predictor, focused on the known failure mode: RVFI `pc_next` and recovery alignment rather than broader predictor machinery.","time":{"start":1778697803479,"end":1778697804786},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_04c4007e8c7390b3016a04c64b5ea0819ab5e702cfc2c989ef","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778697834558,"sessionID":"ses_1dd5ab962ffe7sy5d62I3tzI0B","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_RQATRcgVI2Z2qKwWaVkvBFcJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@\n-title: Minimal not-taken predictor cleanup\n+title: Guarded hot-loop predictor retry\n category: predictor\n motivation: |\n   Prior predictor attempts for this core have consistently regressed or broken\n   because target adders, tags, counters, RAS state, or predicted-PC metadata\n   lengthened hot fetch/decode/control paths. The only predictor already present\n-  and essentially free is static sequential fetch: conditional branches are\n-  predicted not taken by default. The remaining predictor opportunity should\n-  therefore avoid any IF-side target computation or learned state.\n+  and essentially free is static sequential fetch, but CoreMark still pays two\n+  bubbles on every taken loop-closing branch. The one predictor angle still\n+  worth testing is a corrected, extremely small hot-loop predictor that avoids\n+  target arithmetic in fetch and explicitly fixes the prior pc_fwd failure.\n hypothesis: |\n-  Reframe the front end as an explicit static not-taken predictor and make the\n-  smallest possible EX-side cleanup around it: for resolved control transfers,\n-  suppress the pipeline flush only when the resolved next PC is exactly the\n-  sequential pc+4 that the existing fetch path already predicted. Do not add a\n-  BTB, RAS, counters, branch immediate decode in IF, or predicted-PC fields in\n-  pipeline bundles. If implemented narrowly in ex_stage, this can recover rare\n-  false redirect bubbles without perturbing the fetch path or RVFI retirement;\n-  if the needed comparator sits on the branch critical path, it should be\n-  abandoned quickly because the prior broader fall-through-elision attempt\n-  regressed.\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained predictor for one taken backward conditional\n+  branch, but constrain the implementation around the last broken attempt's\n+  failure mode. IF only compares the current PC against one registered branch\n+  PC and selects one registered target; it performs no instruction decode,\n+  target addition, counters, or RAS work. Carry predicted_valid and\n+  predicted_next_pc through IF/ID and ID/EX, and in EX suppress redirect only\n+  when the branch is valid, actually taken, and its resolved target exactly\n+  matches predicted_next_pc. On predicted-taken loop exit, invalidate the entry\n+  and redirect to pc+4 while reporting rvfi pc_next as pc+4 for that retiring\n+  branch. This narrow retry targets the most valuable CoreMark control hazard\n+  while making RVFI pc_fwd consistency an explicit design constraint.\n expected_impact:\n-  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n   confidence: low\n changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add only predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to IF/ID and ID/EX for exact EX-stage validation and RVFI pc_next reporting.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a one-entry EX-trained hot-loop predictor using only current-PC equality and a stored target mux on the fetch path.\"\n   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n-    description: \"Gate redirect with a resolved-target-versus-pc-plus-four check so the existing static not-taken prediction is not flushed when it was already correct.\"\n+    description: \"Train, invalidate, and validate the predictor only for taken backward conditional branches while preserving correct redirect and RVFI pc_next behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor hit metadata and EX training/update signals without changing the NRET=1 top-level interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/b