{"type":"text","timestamp":1778698745779,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b96bfffeNDdnxTkSFCtpWy","part":{"id":"prt_e22b4ede3001d95vzRv0dcMDEb","messageID":"msg_e22b49d390015pdl5dNHFYJ8rI","sessionID":"ses_1dd4b96bfffeNDdnxTkSFCtpWy","type":"text","text":"The predictor history is consistently negative when fetch/decode gains add target adders, tags, counters, RAS state, or predicted-PC metadata. I’m going to write a low-risk predictor hypothesis that keeps prediction off the same-cycle fetch path: a registered one-cycle-ahead loop predictor using stored prebranch PC, branch PC, and target.","time":{"start":1778698743267,"end":1778698745778},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d55238c052ee4bf016a04c9f726b8819b88b6287e09db2b2d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778698783015,"sessionID":"ses_1dd4b96bfffeNDdnxTkSFCtpWy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_bSsYHggTG6SQ3CkakKHqPEHo","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Registered prebranch loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts mostly lost because the prediction decision sat on the\n+  same-cycle fetch next-PC path: immediate decode, target adders, tag compares,\n+  counters, RAS muxes, or current-PC BTB compares lengthened Fmax-critical logic.\n+  CoreMark still pays repeated taken-loop redirect bubbles, so the remaining\n+  useful predictor angle is to predict one cycle before the loop branch reaches\n+  fetch and keep the branch-cycle PC update path nearly as simple as today.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Train a single-entry loop predictor from resolved taken backward conditional\n+  branches in EX, but store both the branch PC and the preceding sequential PC\n+  (branch_pc - 4) along with the resolved target. IF compares the current PC\n+  against the stored prebranch PC and registers a pending prediction for the next\n+  cycle; when the branch PC is fetched, the next-PC mux uses only that registered\n+  pending bit and stored target, not a same-cycle tag compare or target adder.\n+  Carry minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to EX so a correct\n+  prediction suppresses the normal redirect, while loop exit invalidates the\n+  entry and redirects to pc+4 with RVFI pc_next kept consistent. This targets the\n+  hot backward-branch case while moving the predictor compare off the branch\n+  fetch cycle, addressing the main Fmax failure mode of previous predictor tries.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to IF/ID and ID/EX payloads for one-cycle-ahead loop prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single trained prebranch-PC entry, register pending loop predictions one cycle before the branch, and choose the stored target only from the pending bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the IF prediction metadata through decode alongside the existing instruction, PC, operands, and control fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train and invalidate the loop entry from resolved backward branches, suppress redirects on exact predicted-taken matches, and recover correctly on loop exits or mismatches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor training, prediction metadata, and redirect arbitration without changing the NRET=1 top-level RVFI or memory port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Registered prebranch loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts mostly lost because the prediction decision sat on the\n+  same-cycle fetch next-PC path: immediate decode, target adders, tag compares,\n+  counters, RAS muxes, or current-PC BTB compares