{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778699873663,"sessionID":"ses_1dd3ade52ffeF6Xz7qFVnga0K8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_D1mR5jF0V9ozIZh52SUdwdjv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Static not-taken fast path\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core have consistently regressed or broken\n+  because they added fetch-side target adders, tag compares, predicted-PC\n+  metadata, return-stack state, or decode-stage redirect arbitration. The only\n+  predictor that has not hurt timing is the one already implicit in the core:\n+  sequential static not-taken fetch for conditional branches. The remaining\n+  predictor opportunity is therefore to make that static predictor cheaper in\n+  EX rather than add new prediction state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX branch resolution around the static not-taken fast path. For\n+  conditional branches, compute the resolved next PC as pc+4 by default and\n+  only feed the branch-target adder result into redirect and RVFI pc_next when\n+  the branch condition is true. Keep jumps, JALR, misalignment traps, RVFI\n+  reporting, and the existing flush/stall policy unchanged. This does not save\n+  taken-branch bubbles, but it may shorten the common not-taken branch/control\n+  cone and reduce target-adder fanout without any IF predictor mux, stored\n+  target, predicted-PC payload, or new recovery path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Bias branch next-PC and redirect logic toward the existing static not-taken prediction, using the target adder only on taken conditional branches while preserving RVFI pc_next semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Static not-taken fast path\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core have consistently regressed or broken\n+  because they added fetch-side target adders, tag compares, predicted-PC\n+  metadata, return-stack state, or decode-stage redirect arbitration. The only\n+  predictor that has not hurt timing is the one already implicit in the core:\n+  sequential static not-taken fetch for conditional branches. The remaining\n+  predictor opportunity is therefore to make that static predictor cheaper in\n+  EX rather than add new prediction state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX branch resolution around the static not-taken fast path. For\n+  conditional branches, compute the resolved next PC as pc+4 by default and\n+  only feed the branch-target adder result into redirect and RVFI pc_next when\n+  the branch condition is true. Keep jumps, JALR, misalignment traps, RVFI\n+  reporting, and the existing flush/stall policy unchanged. This does not save\n+  taken-branch bubbles, but it may shorten the common not-taken branch/control\n+  cone and reduce target-adder fanout without any IF predictor mux, stored\n+  target, predicted-PC payload, or new recovery path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  -