{"type":"text","timestamp":1778700517544,"sessionID":"ses_1dd308448ffeBopBjpMsUBuBU4","part":{"id":"prt_e22cfcc5e001SklV5etXPOcZsq","messageID":"msg_e22cfa71e001KqTudhqnd8U3Qo","sessionID":"ses_1dd308448ffeBopBjpMsUBuBU4","type":"text","text":"The predictor history is uniformly negative when adding fetch/decode prediction machinery. I’m choosing a minimal predictor-oriented hypothesis that avoids new IF target adders/tags and instead narrows the existing static not-taken policy to reduce taken-branch penalty only for unconditional `JAL` via EX redirect gating? Wait recent JAL tried failed. Better propose \"no new predictor state: branch-likely fallthrough commit? already regressed\". Need title unique. Hmm.\n\nNeed think: One promising predictor angle in exhausted landscape. Maybe \"predict not-taken and avoid flushing ID on not-taken\"? Already no redirect if not taken. Current flush only redirect. No.\n\nMaybe use \"branch target precompute in ID for branch only but no redirect until EX\"? Not predictor category? Could improve Fmax? Actually predictor. Need predict? Maybe \"predecoded sequential branch class to skip branch_target add for not branch\"? Recent static fast path regression gating adder. Hmm.\n\nMaybe \"predict unconditional JAL in IF with stored immediate? failed. RAS failed. BTB failed. Decode variants failed. Single prebranch broken.\"\n\nMaybe propose \"specialize CoreMark loop: one-entry prebranch predictor retry with fix?\" r13s2 broken. Could propose corrected with formal constraints? But recent broken and r12s2 probably maybe? Need log maybe outcomes for r12s2? Grep line truncated no outcome. Could read around maybe only JSON single line. Not needed.\n\nNeed write YAML. Need maybe commentary correction? Avoid messy. Need coherent. Candidate: \"Predicted redirect queue for learned hot loop\" with registered prebranch but guard. But recent registered prebranch broken. Hypothesis can address broken failure likely implementation bug not bad idea. The prompt says single most promising predictor angle. Given \"registered prebranch loop predictor\" broken recent; probably promising if fixed because addresses Fmax compare issue. Propose corrected version with explicit pending prediction cancellation under stalls/redirect and RVFI pc_next consistency. Expected impact 3 low. Changes core_pkg, if_stage, ex_stage, core.\n\nNeed apply_patch.","time":{"start":1778700504158,"end":1778700517543},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_094bc44ff725c6aa016a04d0d800c8819bbb15fe9d39dc8b79","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778700537068,"sessionID":"ses_1dd308448ffeBopBjpMsUBuBU4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_BOyR8EeifNyGxYMnAFAcn1BB","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: \"Stall-safe prebranch loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts usually lost fitness by adding same-cycle fetch target\n+  adders, tag arrays, counters, RAS state, or decode-stage redirect arbitration.\n+  The best remaining predictor angle is still the hot CoreMark loop-closing\n+  branch, but the implementation must keep the branch-fetch PC path simple and\n+  explicitly avoid the stale-prediction and RVFI pc_next failure modes seen in\n+  earlier single-entry loop predictor retries.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-branch predictor that stores branch_pc,\n+  prebranch_pc = branch_pc - 4, and the resolved target. IF compares the current\n+  PC against prebranch_pc and registers a one-cycle pending prediction; when the\n+  following branch PC is actually fetched, the next-PC mux uses only that pending\n+  bit and the stored target, not a same-cycle tag compare, immediate decode, or\n+  target adder. The pending bit must advance only when IF advances, be cleared on\n+  stalls/flushes/redirects, and be carried to EX so correct predicted-taken loop\n+  branches suppress the normal redirect while loop exits invalidate the entry and\n+  redirect to pc+4 with RVFI pc_next matching the next retired instruction.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement the single-entry prebranch predictor with stall-safe pending-bit update and redirect/flush clearing.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train and invalidate the predictor from resolved backward conditional branches and suppress redirects only on exact predicted-taken matches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor train/invalidate signals between EX and IF without changing the NRET=1 top-level interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: \"Stall-safe prebranch loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts usually lost fitness by adding same-cycle fetch target\n+  adders, tag arrays, counters, RAS state, or decode-stage redirect arbitration.\n+  The best remaining predictor angle is still the hot CoreMark loop-closing\n+  branch, but the implementation must keep the branch-fetch PC path simple and\n+  explicitly avoid the stale-prediction and RVFI pc_next failure modes seen in\n+  earlier single-entry loop predictor retries.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-branch predictor that stores branch_pc,\n+  prebranch_pc = branch_pc - 4, and the resolved target. IF compares the current\n+  PC against prebranch_pc and registers a one-cycle pending prediction; when the\n+  following branch PC is actually fetched, the next-PC mux uses only that pending\n+  bit and 