{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778700542393,"sessionID":"ses_1dd308448ffeBopBjpMsUBuBU4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_efWqa5OlpTbDpPsVr278VUJT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n2: title: \"Stall-safe prebranch loop predictor\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Prior predictor attempts usually lost fitness by adding same-cycle fetch target\n6:   adders, tag arrays, counters, RAS state, or decode-stage redirect arbitration.\n7:   The best remaining predictor angle is still the hot CoreMark loop-closing\n8:   branch, but the implementation must keep the branch-fetch PC path simple and\n9:   explicitly avoid the stale-prediction and RVFI pc_next failure modes seen in\n10:   earlier single-entry loop predictor retries.\n11: hypothesis: |\n12:   Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-branch predictor that stores branch_pc,\n13:   prebranch_pc = branch_pc - 4, and the resolved target. IF compares the current\n14:   PC against prebranch_pc and registers a one-cycle pending prediction; when the\n15:   following branch PC is actually fetched, the next-PC mux uses only that pending\n16:   bit and the stored target, not a same-cycle tag compare, immediate decode, or\n17:   target adder. The pending bit must advance only when IF advances, be cleared on\n18:   stalls/flushes/redirects, and be carried to EX so correct predicted-taken loop\n19:   branches suppress the normal redirect while loop exits invalidate the entry and\n20:   redirect to pc+4 with RVFI pc_next matching the next retired instruction.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 3\n23:   confidence: low\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n26:     description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n28:     description: \"Implement the single-entry prebranch predictor with stall-safe pending-bit update and redirect/flush clearing.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Train and invalidate the predictor from resolved backward conditional branches and suppress redirects only on exact predicted-taken matches.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n32:     description: \"Wire predictor train/invalidate signals between EX and IF without changing the NRET=1 top-level interface.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\ntitle: \"Stall-safe prebranch loop predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Prior predictor attempts usually lost fitness by adding same-cycle fetch target\n  adders, tag arrays, counters, RAS state, or decode-stage redirect arbitration.\n  The best remaining predictor angle is still the hot CoreMark loop-closing\n  branch, but the implementation must keep the branch-fetch PC path simple and\n  explicitly avoid the stale-prediction and RVFI pc_next failure modes seen in\n  earlier single-entry loop predictor retries.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a single-entry EX-trained backward-branch predictor that stores branch_pc,\n  prebranch_pc = branch_pc - 4, and the resolved target. IF compares the current\n  PC against prebranch_pc and registers a one-cycle pending prediction; when the\n  following branch PC is actually fetched, the next-PC mux uses only that pending\n  bit and the stored target, not a same-cycle tag compare, immediate decode, or\n  target adder. The pending bit must advance only when IF advances, be cleared on\n  stalls/flushes/redirects, and be carried to EX so correct predicted-taken loop\n  branches suppress the normal redirect while loop exits invalidate the entry and\n  redirect to pc+4 with RVFI pc_next matching the next retired instruction.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778700542387,"end":1778700542392}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03d54a64965a3465016a04d0fbb61c819bb5ee45c64eaa2e5d"}},"id":"prt_e22d057ae0017oqYeBU1fJ6k5g","sessionID":"ses_1dd308448ffeBopBjpMsUBuBU4","messageID":"msg_e22d04d78001jlbPvhHKYFsjY2"}}
