{"type":"text","timestamp":1778677752534,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c329fffe4DpFamKKjtbVj6","part":{"id":"prt_e21749c7e00102iwFiHSz8F4j4","messageID":"msg_e21746ccb0026yd2LXqGvUOllf","sessionID":"ses_1de8c329fffe4DpFamKKjtbVj6","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a predictor-only hypothesis: add a small static BTFNT front-end predictor that redirects fetch for backward loop branches before EX, while preserving EX-stage mispredict recovery and RVFI retirement semantics.","time":{"start":1778677750910,"end":1778677752532},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a1661ab684abcd1016a0477f6cd588198b9c8c5e6e14fdf70","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778677772259,"sessionID":"ses_1de8c329fffe4DpFamKKjtbVj6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_PW0qXSsk33JuYeyp6iNuxBt2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static BTFNT branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core always fetches sequentially and resolves every branch or jump in EX, so each taken loop branch pays a two-instruction front-end flush. CoreMark has tight loops and many backward branches, making a small static predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without adding much FPGA area or hurting the ALU critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an IF-stage static backward-taken/forward-not-taken predictor using the fetched instruction bits to compute B-type targets for negative branch immediates, and optionally early-predict JAL targets because they are unconditional PC-relative redirects. Carry the predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX redirects only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction; mispredicted forward-taken branches, not-taken backward branches, and JALR still recover through the existing flush path. This should remove most loop-closing branch bubbles while preserving the single-retire RVFI contract because retirement remains unchanged at MEM/WB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles with the predicted next PC needed for EX-stage mispredict detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement static BTFNT next-PC selection for backward conditional branches and early PC-relative JAL prediction from fetched instruction bits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch and forward the predicted next PC alongside the decoded instruction without changing decode legality rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved next PC against the carried prediction and assert redirect only on misprediction, while keeping JALR and misalignment trap handling precise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the unchanged redirect interface to the updated predictor-aware IF/ID/EX pipeline behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static BTFNT branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core always fetches sequentially and resolves every branch or jump in EX, so each taken loop branch pays a two-instruction front-end flush. CoreMark has tight loops and many backward branches, making a small static predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without adding much FPGA area or hurting the ALU critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an IF-stage static backward-taken/forward-not-taken predictor using the fetched instruction bits to compute B-type targets for negative branch immediates, and optionally early-predict JAL targets because they are unconditional PC-relative redirects. Carry the predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX redirects only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction; mispredicted forward-taken branches, not-taken backward branches, and JALR still recover through the existing flush path. This should remove most loop-closing branch bubbles while preserving the single-retire RVFI contract because retirement remains unchanged at MEM/WB.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Extend IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles with the predicted next PC needed for EX-stage mispredict detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement static BTFNT next-PC selection for backward conditional branches and early PC-relative JAL prediction from fetched instruction bits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch and forward the predicted next PC alongside the decoded instruction without changing decode legality rules.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved next PC against the carried prediction and assert redirect only on misprediction, while keeping JALR and misalignment trap handling precise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the unchanged redirect interface to the updated predictor-aware IF/ID/EX pipeline behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/c