ughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common taken-control penalty from two bubbles to one while preserving RVFI order, trap reporting, and single-channel retirement.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire ID-stage early redirect signals into the IF and hazard path while preserving the existing NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add early branch/JAL/JALR resolution using decoded control, immediates, regfile operands, and forwarded compare/base operands.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/forward_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Extend forwarding ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n4: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-003-r1s2\", \"title\": \"Static BTFNT branch predictor\", \"category\": \"predictor\", \"motivation\": \"The current five-stage core always fetches sequentially and resolves every branch or jump in EX, so each taken loop branch pays a two-instruction front-end flush. CoreMark has tight loops and many backward branches, making a small static predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without adding much FPGA area or hurting the ALU critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current five-stage core always fetches sequentially and resolves every branch or jump in EX, so each taken loop branch pays a two-instruction front-end flush. CoreMark has tight loops and many backward branches, making a small static predictor likely to improve iterations per cycle without adding much FPGA area or hurting the ALU critical path.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Add an IF-stage static backward-taken/forward-not-taken predictor using the fetched instruction bits to compute B-type targets for negative branch immediates, and optionally early-predict JAL targets because they are unconditional PC-relative redirects. Carry the predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX redirects only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction; mispredicted forward-taken branches, not-taken backward branches, and JALR still recover through the existing flush path. This should remove most loop-closing branch bubbles while preserving the single-retire RVFI contract because retirement remains unchanged at MEM/WB.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core_pkg.sv\", \"description\": \"Extend IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles with the predicted next PC needed for EX-stage mispredict detection.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/if_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Implement static BTFNT next-PC selection for backward conditional branches and early PC-relative JAL prediction from fetched instruction bits.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Lat... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(End of file - total 4 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"baseline-bench-5327bba\", \"title\": \"Baseline retest for cores/bench\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"outcome\": \"improvement\", \"fitness\": 282.82, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 127.03, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9563, \"ff\": 1866, \"seeds\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-13T13:08:01.185076Z\", \"round_id\": 0, \"slot\": 0}\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-001-r1s0\", \"title\": \"Multicycle RV32M arithmetic unit\", \"category\": \"micro_opt\", \"motivation\": \"The current ALU computes every multiply and divide result combinationally in\\nthe EX stage, including signed and unsigned 64-bit products plus divider and\\nremainder operators. That wide arithmetic cone is a likely Fmax limiter on\\nTang Nano 20K, while CoreMark's hot path should not need single-cycle DIV/REM\\nthroughput. Trading rare M-extension latency for a shorter common EX critical\\npath should improve iterations/second through higher clock frequency.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The current ALU computes every multiply and divide result combinationally in\\nthe EX stage, including signed and unsigned 64-bit products plus divider and\\nremainder operators. That wide arithmetic cone is a likely Fmax limiter on\\nTang Nano 20K, while CoreMark's hot path should not need single-cycle DIV/REM\\nthroughput. Trading rare M-extension latency for a shorter common EX critical\\npath should improve iterations/second through higher clock frequency.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Split RV32M operations out of the always-combinational ALU path behind a\\nsmall multicycle M-unit handshake in EX. Keep ADD/SUB/logic/branch/address\\noperations purely combinational, but when the decoded alu_op is MUL/DIV/REM,\\nhold ID/EX and EX/MEM until the iterative arithmetic result is ready, then\\nretire normally through the existing MEM/WB and RVFI path. This should remove\\ndivider and large multiplier logic from the ordinary EX-stage timing path;\\nthe added stalls only affect uncommon M instructions and should be outweighed\\nby improved Fmax on the FPGA fitness metric.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 6, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Restrict the combinational ALU to fast RV32I operations and expose only lightweight M-op selection or helper logic needed by the new M-unit.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add a multicycl... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"id\": \"hyp-20260513-002-r1s1\", \"title\": \"Resolve control flow in ID\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"CoreMark spends a significant fraction of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"CoreMark spends a significant fraction of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common taken-control penalty from two bubbles to one while preserving RVFI order, trap reporting, and single-channel retirement.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 8, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire ID-stage early redirect signals into the IF and hazard path while preserving the existing NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/id_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Add early branch/JAL/JALR resolution using 