{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778678995728,"sessionID":"ses_1de7940d2ffeyK0MHkwxKUwbJa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_qdqA8raJmRqNpohGZHLf0i1J","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Tiny return-address stack predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The prior static BTFNT predictor targeted loop branches but put branch immediate decode\n+  and target adders directly on the IF PC-update path, regressing the CoreMark fitness\n+  despite saving some bubbles. CoreMark still has frequent function calls and returns,\n+  and the current core pays the same EX-stage redirect penalty for every JALR return.\n+  A tiny return predictor can attack those bubbles without adding branch-target arithmetic\n+  to fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small 4-entry return-address stack that predicts only canonical returns\n+  (JALR x0, 0(x1/x5)) in IF. Push pc+4 for link-register calls when they resolve,\n+  pop/predict the stack top for returns, and carry the predicted next PC through the\n+  pipeline so EX redirects only on mismatch. This keeps ordinary branch fetch as pc+4,\n+  avoids B-type immediate decode and target adders in the IF critical path, and should\n+  recover part of the call/return control-flow penalty with modest LUT/FF cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC and return-predicted metadata to IF/ID, ID/EX, and EX/MEM bundles for mispredict detection and RAS bookkeeping.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect canonical return encodings in the fetched instruction and select the RAS top as the next PC only when the stack is nonempty.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved JALR targets against the carried prediction, redirect on mismatch, and expose resolved call/return events for RAS update.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate the tiny RAS, wire prediction inputs to IF, update it from resolved control-flow events, and preserve the NRET=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat return-prediction mismatches like existing EX redirects so wrong-path IF/ID and ID/EX state is flushed without changing data-hazard behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r2s2\n+title: \"Tiny return-address stack predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The prior static BTFNT predictor targeted loop branches but put branch immediate decode\n+  and target adders directly on the IF PC-update path, regressing the CoreMark fitness\n+  despite saving some bubbles. CoreMark still has frequent function calls and returns,\n+  and the current core pays the same EX-stage redirect penalty for every JALR return.\n+  A tiny return predictor can attack those bubbles without adding branch-target arithmetic\n+  to fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small 4-entry return-address stack that predicts only canonical returns\n+  (JALR x0, 0(x1/x5)) in IF. Push pc+4 for link-register calls when they resolve,\n+  pop/predict the stack top for returns, and carry the predicted next PC through the\n+  pipeline so EX redirects only on mismatch. This keeps ordinary branch fetch as pc+4,\n+  avoids B-type immediate decode and target adders in the IF critical path, and should\n+  recover part of the call/return control-flow penalty with modest LUT/FF cost.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC and return-predicted metadata to IF/ID, ID/EX, and EX/MEM bundles for mispredict detection and RAS bookkeeping.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect canonical return encodings in the fetched instruction and select the RAS top as the next PC only when the stack is nonempty.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved JALR targets against the carried prediction, redirect on mismatch, and expose resolved call/return events for RAS update.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate the tiny RAS, wire prediction inputs to IF, update it from resolved control-flow events, and preserve the NRET=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat return-prediction mismatches like existing EX redirects so wrong-path IF/ID and ID/EX state is flushed without changing data-hazard behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513