{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778680513426,"sessionID":"ses_1de624aedffeUTdz1TO7ZXsmCS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_glKjJteqGwFKC9cw1j6QuBni","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage JAL predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The prior predictor attempts regressed because they placed branch target decode,\n+  target adders, return detection, and prediction muxes directly on the IF PC path.\n+  CoreMark still pays the existing EX redirect penalty for every unconditional JAL,\n+  and JAL targets are PC-relative with no register dependency or branch condition.\n+  Predicting only JAL in decode should recover one control-flow bubble for calls and\n+  long jumps while avoiding the risky fetch-path predictor logic that hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a narrow decode-stage always-taken predictor for legal JAL instructions only.\n+  ID computes pc+imm for JAL, redirects fetch one cycle before EX would, and records\n+  the predicted next PC in the ID/EX bundle. EX then suppresses the normal JAL redirect\n+  when the resolved jump target matches the predicted target, but retains the existing\n+  EX recovery path for conditional branches, JALR, illegal instructions, and any target\n+  mismatch. Because the predictor excludes branches and returns, it needs no B-type\n+  immediate decode in IF, no RAS state, and no operand forwarding, making it a smaller\n+  predictor angle with a better chance of improving CoreMark iterations/cycle without\n+  sacrificing the current high Fmax.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID or ID/EX pipeline bundle so EX can distinguish an already-predicted JAL from an unpredicted redirect.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect legal JAL after decode, compute the PC-relative target from the existing immediate, drive an early redirect, and latch the predicted target metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage JAL redirect into IF and hazard flushing with priority below reset and alongside the existing EX redirect path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress the normal JAL redirect when the decoded prediction matches the resolved jump target; keep branch, JALR, misalignment, and mismatch recovery unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage JAL predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The prior predictor attempts regressed because they placed branch target decode,\n+  target adders, return detection, and prediction muxes directly on the IF PC path.\n+  CoreMark still pays the existing EX redirect penalty for every unconditional JAL,\n+  and JAL targets are PC-relative with no register dependency or branch condition.\n+  Predicting only JAL in decode should recover one control-flow bubble for calls and\n+  long jumps while avoiding the risky fetch-path predictor logic that hurt Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a narrow decode-stage always-taken predictor for legal JAL instructions only.\n+  ID computes pc+imm for JAL, redirects fetch one cycle before EX would, and records\n+  the predicted next PC in the ID/EX bundle. EX then suppresses the normal JAL redirect\n+  when the resolved jump target matches the predicted target, but retains the existing\n+  EX recovery path for conditional branches, JALR, illegal instructions, and any target\n+  mismatch. Because the predictor excludes branches and returns, it needs no B-type\n+  immediate decode in IF, no RAS state, and no operand forwarding, making it a smaller\n+  predictor angle with a better chance of improving CoreMark iterations/cycle without\n+  sacrificing the current high Fmax.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID or ID/EX pipeline bundle so EX can distinguish an already-predicted JAL from an unpredicted redirect.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect legal JAL after decode, compute the PC-relative target from the existing immediate, drive an early redirect, and latch the predicted target metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage JAL redirect into IF and hazard flushing with priority below reset and alongside the existing EX redirect path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress the normal JAL redirect when the decoded prediction matches the resolved jump target; keep branch, JALR, misalignment, and mismatch recovery unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260