{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778682608191,"sessionID":"ses_1de422ec2ffe6JS8OyGoYg3GLY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_eHskaI6YwucLH2tuqi0Rogks","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r4s2\n+title: \"Tiny resolved-target BTB\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves all taken branches and jumps in EX, so tight CoreMark loops pay a two-bubble redirect penalty. Prior predictor attempts regressed because they decoded immediates, computed targets, or managed return-stack state on the front-end critical path. A small BTB trained from already-resolved EX redirects can target the same loop bubbles while avoiding fetch-stage target arithmetic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped branch target buffer that stores resolved taken conditional-branch targets, preferably only backward loop branches, along with a compact PC tag and a 2-bit confidence counter. IF predicts to the stored target on a tag hit with a taken counter, otherwise it keeps the existing pc+4 path; EX updates the BTB after branch resolution and flushes on any predicted/resolved next-PC mismatch. Because the target is stored from the prior execution, the fetch path adds only a small tag compare and next-PC mux instead of B/J immediate decode and target adders, which should recover loop-closing branch bubbles with less Fmax damage than the previous predictor attempts.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Carry predicted next-PC metadata through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can distinguish correct BTB predictions from mispredictions without changing the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a very small EX-trained BTB lookup on the PC, select the stored target only on a valid tag hit with a taken counter, and keep the default sequential fetch path otherwise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved branch next-PC against the carried prediction, redirect only on mismatch, and emit compact BTB update information for resolved conditional branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire BTB prediction metadata and EX update signals between IF and EX while preserving the existing single-channel RVFI ports.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r4s2\n+title: \"Tiny resolved-target BTB\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core resolves all taken branches and jumps in EX, so tight CoreMark loops pay a two-bubble redirect penalty. Prior predictor attempts regressed because they decoded immediates, computed targets, or managed return-stack state on the front-end critical path. A small BTB trained from already-resolved EX redirects can target the same loop bubbles while avoiding fetch-stage target arithmetic.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped branch target buffer that stores resolved taken conditional-branch targets, preferably only backward loop branches, along with a compact PC tag and a 2-bit confidence counter. IF predicts to the stored target on a tag hit with a taken counter, otherwise it keeps the existing pc+4 path; EX updates the BTB after branch resolution and flushes on any predicted/resolved next-PC mismatch. Because the target is stored from the prior execution, the fetch path adds only a small tag compare and next-PC mux instead of B/J immediate decode and target adders, which should recover loop-closing branch bubbles with less Fmax damage than the previous predictor attempts.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Carry predicted next-PC metadata through IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can distinguish correct BTB predictions from mispredictions without changing the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a very small EX-trained BTB lookup on the PC, select the stored target only on a valid tag hit with a taken counter, and keep the default sequential fetch path otherwise.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved branch next-PC against the carried prediction, redirect only on mismatch, and emit compact BTB update information for resolved conditional branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire BTB prediction metadata and EX update signals between IF and EX while preserving the existing single-channel RVFI ports.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.ya