{"type":"text","timestamp":1778684886891,"sessionID":"ses_1de1f1a2fffeDc6ylGcZER8Nlw","part":{"id":"prt_e21e17d3200135CzaBu6YwJKUB","messageID":"msg_e21e11ec0001OcT45MB14VAWfO","sessionID":"ses_1de1f1a2fffeDc6ylGcZER8Nlw","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently lost fitness when they added target arithmetic, arrays, counters, or return-stack logic to fetch. The narrowest remaining predictor angle is a single-entry resolved-loop target predictor: no immediate decode in IF, no counter RAM, just one PC compare and stored target for the current hot backward branch.","time":{"start":1778684886323,"end":1778684886889},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_059f13ded6f2fe43016a0493d633b8819ba1f39e6c8a67f50f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778684906324,"sessionID":"ses_1de1f1a2fffeDc6ylGcZER8Nlw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_pQbBnxoLBE9rLXD001iBQiDS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Single-entry loop target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core fetches sequentially and pays the existing EX-stage redirect\n+  penalty on every taken loop-closing branch. Earlier predictor attempts\n+  regressed because they placed immediate decode, target adders, BTB arrays,\n+  counters, or RAS control on the fetch path. A predictor for this slot should\n+  therefore be much narrower: reuse targets already resolved in EX and add the\n+  smallest possible fetch-side structure.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry resolved-loop target predictor trained only by taken\n+  backward conditional branches. The entry stores one branch PC and its resolved\n+  target; IF predicts taken only when the current PC equals that stored PC,\n+  otherwise it keeps the existing pc+4 behavior. Carry predicted-taken and\n+  predicted-next-PC metadata to EX so the normal redirect path fires only on a\n+  mismatch, and invalidate the entry when that same branch resolves not-taken\n+  at loop exit. This should recover repeated inner-loop branch bubbles in\n+  CoreMark while avoiding the fetch target adders, multi-entry tag arrays,\n+  confidence counters, and return-stack machinery that hurt prior predictors.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-taken and predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX-stage mismatch detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a single stored branch-PC/target entry with one equality compare and target mux; update/invalidate it from resolved EX branch feedback.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress redirects when the single-entry prediction matches the resolved branch target, and report update information for taken backward branches and loop exits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire resolved branch predictor update signals between EX and IF without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO or RVFI retirement boundary.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Single-entry loop target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current core fetches sequentially and pays the existing EX-stage redirect\n+  penalty on every taken loop-closing branch. Earlier predictor attempts\n+  regressed because they placed immediate decode, target adders, BTB arrays,\n+  counters, or RAS control on the fetch path. A predictor for this slot should\n+  therefore be much narrower: reuse targets already resolved in EX and add the\n+  smallest possible fetch-side structure.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry resolved-loop target predictor trained only by taken\n+  backward conditional branches. The entry stores one branch PC and its resolved\n+  target; IF predicts taken only when the current PC equals that stored PC,\n+  otherwise it keeps the existing pc+4 behavior. Carry predicted