{"type":"text","timestamp":1778687330101,"sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c2e0ffen6zmBpNmqkD6vT","part":{"id":"prt_e2206beca001HH85c1ibUlhw2M","messageID":"msg_e22066b22001vy3EftbRuj3pPJ","sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c2e0ffen6zmBpNmqkD6vT","type":"text","text":"Predictor history is uniformly negative when prediction logic adds IF target arithmetic, multi-entry tags/counters, or return metadata. The narrowest remaining predictor angle is to train only unconditional `JAL` targets from EX resolution and use a single exact-PC entry, avoiding branch condition prediction and fetch-side immediate adders.","time":{"start":1778687327946,"end":1778687330095},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_03489222b06cb879016a049d5fb488819abb9b837e2033ca10","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778687349871,"sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c2e0ffen6zmBpNmqkD6vT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ElttHTYJoTdFztoiRGQkv0r8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Single-entry JAL target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts regressed because they put immediate decode, target\n+  adders, multi-entry tags, counters, or return-stack control on the fetch path.\n+  CoreMark still pays the EX redirect penalty for repeated unconditional calls\n+  and jumps, but JAL has no direction ambiguity once a target is known. A very\n+  small learned JAL target entry can attack only that control-flow cost while\n+  avoiding conditional branch and return prediction complexity.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry predictor trained only by legal resolved JAL instructions\n+  in EX. The entry stores the exact JAL PC and resolved target; IF predicts to\n+  the stored target only when the current PC equals that entry, otherwise it\n+  keeps the existing pc+4 path. Carry only predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata to EX so the normal redirect path is suppressed on an exact correct\n+  prediction and used for all misses or mismatches. This should recover repeated\n+  call/jump bubbles in CoreMark without fetch-side immediate decode, B-type\n+  branch prediction, return-stack state, confidence counters, or multi-entry BTB\n+  routing that hurt previous predictor hypotheses.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX-stage JAL prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a single exact-PC JAL target entry with pc-match next-PC selection and EX-trained update inputs, without decoding immediates in fetch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the JAL target entry from resolved legal JALs and suppress the existing jump redirect only when the carried prediction exactly matches the resolved next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the JAL predictor update and prediction metadata between IF and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Single-entry JAL target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts regressed because they put immediate decode, target\n+  adders, multi-entry tags, counters, or return-stack control on the fetch path.\n+  CoreMark still pays the EX redirect penalty for repeated unconditional calls\n+  and jumps, but JAL has no direction ambiguity once a target is known. A very\n+  small learned JAL target entry can attack only that control-flow cost while\n+  avoiding conditional branch and return prediction complexity.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry predictor trained only by legal resolved JAL instructions\n+  in EX. The entry stores the exact JAL PC and resolved target; IF predicts to\n+  the stored target only when the current PC equals that entry, otherwise it\n+  keeps the existing pc+4 path. Carry only predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata to EX so the normal redirect path is suppressed on an exact correct\n+  prediction and used for all misses or mismatches. This should recover repeated\n+  call/jump bubbles in CoreMark without fetch-side immediate decode, B-type\n+  branch prediction, return-stack state, confidence counters, or multi-entry BTB\n+  routing that hurt previous predictor hypotheses.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX-stage JAL prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a single exact-PC JAL target entry with pc-match next-PC selection and EX-trained update inputs, without decoding immediates in fetch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Train the JAL target entry from resolved legal JALs and suppress the existing jump redirect only when the carried prediction exactly matches the resolved next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the JAL predictor update and prediction metadata between IF and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_