{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778687356175,"sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c2e0ffen6zmBpNmqkD6vT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OYN7ZiicdS2bwOGYha7NUz0e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\n2: title: \"Single-entry JAL target predictor\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Prior predictor attempts regressed because they put immediate decode, target\n6:   adders, multi-entry tags, counters, or return-stack control on the fetch path.\n7:   CoreMark still pays the EX redirect penalty for repeated unconditional calls\n8:   and jumps, but JAL has no direction ambiguity once a target is known. A very\n9:   small learned JAL target entry can attack only that control-flow cost while\n10:   avoiding conditional branch and return prediction complexity.\n11: hypothesis: |\n12:   Add a single-entry predictor trained only by legal resolved JAL instructions\n13:   in EX. The entry stores the exact JAL PC and resolved target; IF predicts to\n14:   the stored target only when the current PC equals that entry, otherwise it\n15:   keeps the existing pc+4 path. Carry only predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC\n16:   metadata to EX so the normal redirect path is suppressed on an exact correct\n17:   prediction and used for all misses or mismatches. This should recover repeated\n18:   call/jump bubbles in CoreMark without fetch-side immediate decode, B-type\n19:   branch prediction, return-stack state, confidence counters, or multi-entry BTB\n20:   routing that hurt previous predictor hypotheses.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n23:   confidence: low\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n26:     description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for EX-stage JAL prediction validation.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n28:     description: \"Implement a single exact-PC JAL target entry with pc-match next-PC selection and EX-trained update inputs, without decoding immediates in fetch.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Train the JAL target entry from resolved legal JALs and suppress the existing jump redirect only when the carried prediction exactly matches the resolved next PC.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n32:     description: \"Wire the JAL predictor update and prediction metadata between IF and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level RVFI interface.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r6s2\ntitle: \"Single-entry JAL target predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Prior predictor attempts regressed because they put immediate decode, target\n  adders, multi-entry tags, counters, or return-stack control on the fetch path.\n  CoreMark still pays the EX redirect penalty for repeated unconditional calls\n  and jumps, but JAL has no direction ambiguity once a target is known. A very\n  small learned JAL target entry can attack only that control-flow cost while\n  avoiding conditional branch and return prediction complexity.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a single-entry predictor trained only by legal resolved JAL instructions\n  in EX. The entry stores the exact JAL PC and resolved target; IF predicts to\n  the stored target only when the current PC equals that entry, otherwise it\n  keeps the existing pc+4 path. Carry only predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC\n  metadata to EX so the normal redirect path is suppressed on an exact correct\n  prediction and used for all misses or mismatches. This should recover repeated\n  call/jump bubbles in CoreMark without fetch-side immediate decode, B-type\n  branch prediction, return-stack state, confidence counters, or multi-entry BTB\n  routing that hurt previous predictor hypotheses.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r6s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778687356149,"end":1778687356173}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a8a0b7176b2712b016a049d799a98819a8cda39519729866a"}},"id":"prt_e2207236c001lPrEyZPV9ughbt","sessionID":"ses_1ddf9c2e0ffen6zmBpNmqkD6vT","messageID":"msg_e2207150f001Z3X3O4K79n6U7M"}}
