{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778689147061,"sessionID":"ses_1ddde3fc1ffeo1gpCnBmvbyYFN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_idLcH75pO3SE5hwUjPv7h1MS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Decode-only JAL redirect predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added target\n+  adders, tag compares, return-stack state, or predicted-PC muxing directly to\n+  the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX redirect penalty for\n+  every unconditional JAL, and JAL needs no operand forwarding or direction\n+  prediction once its instruction reaches decode.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage predictor for legal JAL instructions only. ID already has\n+  the instruction, PC, and immediate generator output, so it can compute the JAL\n+  target and redirect fetch one cycle earlier than EX without adding any logic\n+  to the IF PC increment path. Carry a small predicted-next-PC flag/value into\n+  ID/EX so EX suppresses its normal JAL redirect when the ID prediction matches,\n+  while all conditional branches, JALR, illegal instructions, and mismatches use\n+  the existing EX recovery path. This avoids the failed fetch-side predictor\n+  structures while recovering one bubble on CoreMark calls and PC-relative jumps.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to the IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for decode-stage JAL prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect legal JAL in decode, compute pc plus J-immediate, emit an early redirect, and latch the prediction metadata into ID/EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage predicted redirect into the existing IF and hazard redirect path without changing the NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress the normal EX JAL redirect when the carried decode prediction matches the resolved target; keep existing EX redirects for misses and mismatches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat the decode-stage JAL prediction as a redirect/flush source while preserving dmem, imem, load-use, and M-unit stall priorities.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Decode-only JAL redirect predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core regressed because they added target\n+  adders, tag compares, return-stack state, or predicted-PC muxing directly to\n+  the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX redirect penalty for\n+  every unconditional JAL, and JAL needs no operand forwarding or direction\n+  prediction once its instruction reaches decode.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage predictor for legal JAL instructions only. ID already has\n+  the instruction, PC, and immediate generator output, so it can compute the JAL\n+  target and redirect fetch one cycle earlier than EX without adding any logic\n+ 