n of its bracketed runtime in tight loops and conditional control flow. The current five-stage pipeline resolves branches and jumps in EX, then flushes both IF and ID, so every taken branch or jump pays roughly a two-cycle redirect penalty. Reducing that penalty improves iterations/cycle without increasing retirement width or touching the external NRET=1 contract.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": \\\"Move branch and JAL/JALR target/condition resolution from EX into the decode stage, with decode-stage operand forwarding from EX/MEM and MEM/WB for branch compares and JALR base operands. Keep the existing EX-stage trap/metadata path as the retirement source, but let ID drive redirect one cycle earlier when operands are available; stall only for unresolved load-to-branch/JALR dependencies. This should cut the common tak... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n5: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778693360962,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_gDQd38SDsuyFKgZwJOhYWgR2\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":200},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r1s0 (improvement, +32.85%): Moving RV32M multiply/divide out of the combinational EX ALU behind a multicycle handshake can substantially improve FPGA fitness because CoreMark rarely needs M-op throughput while the removed arithmetic cone dominates Fmax.\\n2: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r1s1 (broken, n/a): Moving branch/JALR resolution into ID needs exhaustive operand-valid stalling and forwarding for decode-stage compares/base operands; stale early redirects can let wrong-path state reach writeback, which riscv-formal's reg check catches.\\n3: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r1s2 (regression, +21.76%): IF-stage BTFNT/JAL prediction can regress CoreMark when instruction-bit immediate decode and target adders sit directly on the fetch PC path, so front-end bubble savings must be weighed against Fmax-critical next-PC logic.\\n4: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-001-r2s0 (regression, -1.92%): Replacing MEM-stage variable shifts with explicit byte/halfword lane case muxes did not help FPGA fitness, suggesting the synthesizer already maps these narrow shifts well and the added mux/control structure can slightly worsen routing or LUT packing.\\n5: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-002-r2s1 (regression, -7.79%): A two-entry IF skid buffer did not pay for CoreMark's random imem stalls; the added fetch-valid/control and redirect-flush machinery can cost more FPGA fitness than the front-end bubbles it hides.\\n6: - 2026-05-13 hyp-20260513-003-r2s2 (regression, -44... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n6: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778693361023,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2262cd7c001MNmIVENujY8WUF\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"08cd2a07f0a60939d5f7c3e763feb8bf2a853b3c\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e226294b8001OwkCFYiOQ45oGo\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":38511,\"input\":38210,\"output\":272,\"reasoning\":29,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\n7: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778693362308,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2262d283001qUcSrlFffMLD7o\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2262cdbf001hiYyZAmADAIdDg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ\",\"snapshot\":\"08cd2a07f0a60939d5f7c3e763feb8bf2a853b3c\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n8: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1778693368711,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e2262e6f6001IKge9MNWx6n249\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e2262cdbf001hiYyZAmADAIdDg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses