{"type":"text","timestamp":1778693398737,"sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ","part":{"id":"prt_e226359d2001C8E0jTibFuz7K6","messageID":"msg_e226316e0001ZH6lvWmpAwunFr","sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ","type":"text","text":"The previous JAL-only decode predictor also regressed, so I’m pivoting to a different predictor niche: decode-stage static backward-branch prediction. It targets CoreMark loop branches while still keeping prediction target arithmetic out of IF.","time":{"start":1778693396946,"end":1778693398735},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_087a2660f634f500016a04b514cca0819b88d7abd9838e7799","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778693420476,"sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_k86pIubPRM8foHQ9muKaoyt5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts lost fitness when they added BTB, RAS, tag compare,\n+  counter, or target-adder logic to the IF next-PC path. The current core still\n+  pays a two-bubble EX redirect penalty on taken loop-closing branches, which\n+  are the predictor opportunity most likely to matter for CoreMark. A predictor\n+  that waits until decode can use the already-fetched instruction and decoded\n+  branch control while keeping fetch as the current simple pc+4 path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a static decode-stage predictor for legal backward conditional branches\n+  only. ID uses the existing immediate generator and decoded is_branch signal to\n+  recognize negative B-type offsets, computes pc+imm, and redirects fetch one\n+  cycle earlier than EX would. Carry predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC into\n+  ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal redirect when the branch is actually taken\n+  to the predicted target, or redirects to pc+4 on the loop-exit not-taken\n+  misprediction. Forward branches, JAL, JALR, illegal encodings, and all memory\n+  or RVFI behavior stay on the existing path. This targets loop bubbles without\n+  reintroducing the failed IF-side predictor structures.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to the ID/EX bundle for EX-stage branch prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect legal backward conditional branches in decode, compute pc plus B-immediate, emit an early redirect, and latch prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved branch outcome against decode prediction, suppress matching redirects, and recover to pc+4 on predicted-taken loop exits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire decode-stage prediction redirect into the existing IF and hazard flush path without changing the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat decode prediction redirects like other front-end flushes while preserving load-use, dmem stall, imem stall, and M-unit stall priority.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts lost fitness when they added BTB, RAS, tag compare,\n+  counter, or target-adder logic to the IF next-PC path. The current core still\n+  pays a two-bubble EX redirect penalty on taken loop-closing branches, which\n+  are the predictor opportunity most likely to matter for CoreMark. A predictor\n+  that waits until decode can use the already-fetched instruction and decoded\n+  branch control while keeping fetch as the current simple pc+4 path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a static decode-stage predictor for legal backward conditional branches\n+  only. ID uses the existing immediate generator and decoded is_branch signal to\n+  recognize negative B-type offsets, computes pc+imm, and redirects fetch one\n+  cycle earlier than EX would. Carry predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC into\n+  ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal redirect when the branch is actually taken\n+  to the predicted target, or redirects to pc+4 on the loop-exit not-taken\n+  misprediction. Forward branches, JAL, JALR, illegal encodings, and all memory\n+  or RVFI behavior stay on the existing path. This targets loop bubbles without\n+  reintroducing the failed IF-side predictor structures.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC fields to the ID/EX bundle for EX-stage branch prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect legal backward conditional branches in decode, compute pc plus B-immediate, emit an early redirect, and latch prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved branch outcome against decode prediction, suppress matching redirects, and recover to pc+4 on predicted-taken loop exits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire decode-stage prediction redirect into the existing IF and hazard flush path without changing the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat decode prediction redirects like other front-end flushes while preserving load-use, dmem stall, imem stall, and M-unit stall priority.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/ben