ses the normal redirect when the branch is actually taken\n  to the predicted target, or redirects to pc+4 on the loop-exit not-taken\n  misprediction. Forward branches, JAL, JALR, illegal encodings, and all memory\n  or RVFI behavior stay on the existing path. This targets loop bubbles without\n  reintroducing the failed IF-side predictor structures.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778693428579,"end":1778693428592}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04864a814af20f73016a04b53390a8819a8b96656ee623e94d"}},"id":"prt_e2263d1e20014Xt3lsZ8blrPJu","sessionID":"ses_1dd9d6d28ffeJXmrKozX6DrpvQ","messageID":"msg_e2263b7a6001joMcClMfi1cvKQ"}}
