{"type":"text","timestamp":1778695260482,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","part":{"id":"prt_e227fc243001FvjqhaPy1xQxe0","messageID":"msg_e227f7006001PZZz2q8AtQDJLQ","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor attempts consistently lost on fetch-path target logic and prediction metadata, so the new hypothesis should be deliberately narrower: a predictor/control hint that avoids extra IF next-PC adders, BTBs, RAS state, and broad pipeline metadata.","time":{"start":1778695258691,"end":1778695260478},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_09ce06156e3345bf016a04bc5a97b08199827c173f211119d5","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778695279559,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","part":{"id":"prt_e22800e95001Go4s4jLc4FAzaH","messageID":"msg_e227f7006001PZZz2q8AtQDJLQ","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a narrow predictor hypothesis: decode-stage canonical return prediction from the already-read link register, gated off when the return base has an unresolved in-flight producer. This targets call/return bubbles without RAS state or IF-side target computation.","time":{"start":1778695278229,"end":1778695279558},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_09ce06156e3345bf016a04bc6e1e208199a96f600474c68d56","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778695302641,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_s9Dfq0I3RrYII5K7GpPRsrbN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core mostly regressed because they added\n+  target adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack state, or predicted-PC\n+  muxes directly to the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX\n+  redirect penalty on every canonical function return, and CoreMark contains\n+  enough call/return traffic that recovering one redirect cycle there may help\n+  iterations per cycle. A return predictor that operates only after decode can\n+  use the already-fetched instruction, regfile read data, and existing immediate\n+  path while keeping fetch's common pc+4 path untouched.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage predictor for canonical returns only: legal JALR with\n+  rd=x0, funct3=0, imm=0, and rs1=x1 or x5. ID computes the return target from\n+  the already-read link register value and redirects fetch one cycle before EX\n+  would, but only when the base register is not the destination of an unresolved\n+  older instruction in ID/EX or EX/MEM. Carry a minimal predicted-valid and\n+  predicted-next-PC field into ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal JALR redirect\n+  on an exact match and uses the existing recovery redirect on mismatches. This\n+  avoids the failed IF-side RAS/BTB/BTFNT machinery while targeting a narrower\n+  control-flow pattern with no branch direction ambiguity.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to the ID/EX bundle for decode-stage return prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect canonical JALR returns, compute the register-based target from rs1_data plus zero immediate, and emit early redirect metadata only when the base operand is safe.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage return prediction redirect into the existing IF/hazard redirect path and provide in-flight destination qualifiers for safe prediction gating.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved JALR next PC against the decode prediction, suppress correct duplicate redirects, and retain existing EX recovery for mismatches and unpredicted returns.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core mostly regressed because they added\n+  target adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack state, or predicted-PC\n+  muxes directly to the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX\n+  redirect penalty on every canonical function return, and CoreMark contains\n+  enough call/return traffic that recovering one redirect cycle there may help\n+  iterations per cycle. A return predictor that operates only after decode can\n+  use the already-fetched instruction, regfile read data, and existing immediate\n+  path while keeping fetch's common pc+4 path untouched.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage predictor for canonical returns only: legal JALR with\n+  rd=x0, funct3=0, imm=0, and rs1=x1 or x5. ID computes the return target from\n+  the already-read link register value and redirects fetch one cycle before EX\n+  would, but only when the base register is not the destination of an unresolved\n+  older instruction in ID/EX or EX/MEM. Carry a minimal predicted-valid and\n+  predicted-next-PC field into ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal JALR redirect\n+  on an exact match and uses the existing recovery redirect on mismatches. This\n+  avoids the failed IF-side RAS/BTB/BTFNT machinery while targeting a narrower\n+  control-flow pattern with no branch direction ambiguity.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to the ID/EX bundle for decode-stage return prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect canonical JALR returns, compute the register-based target from rs1_data plus zero immediate, and emit early redirect metadata only when the base operand is safe.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage return prediction redirect into the existing IF/hazard redirect path and provide in-flight destination qualifiers for safe prediction gating.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved JALR next PC against the decode prediction, suppress correct duplicate redirects, and retain existing EX recovery for mismatches and unpredicted returns.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts for this core mostly regressed because they added\n+  target adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack state, or predicted-PC\n+  muxes directly to the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX\n+  redirect penalty on every canonical function return, and CoreMark contains\n+  enough call/return traffic that recovering one redirect cycle there may help\n+  iterations per cycle. A return predictor that operates only after decode can\n+  use the already-fetched instruction, regfile read data, and existing immediate\n+  path while keeping fetch's common pc+4 path untouched.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a decode-stage predictor for canonical returns only: legal JALR with\n+  rd=x0, funct3=0, imm=0, and rs1=x1 or x5. ID computes the return target from\n+  the already-read link register value and redirects fetch one cycle before EX\n+  would, but only when the base register is not the destination of an unresolved\n+  older instruction in ID/EX or EX/MEM. Carry a minimal predicted-valid and\n+  predicted-next-PC field into ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal JALR redirect\n+  on an exact match and uses the existing recovery redirect on mismatches. This\n+  avoids the failed IF-side RAS/BTB/BTFNT machinery while targeting a narrower\n+  control-flow pattern with no branch direction ambiguity.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to the ID/EX bundle for decode-stage return prediction validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect canonical JALR returns, compute the register-based target from rs1_data plus zero immediate, and emit early redirect metadata only when the base operand is safe.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire ID-stage return prediction redirect into the existing IF/hazard redirect path and provide in-flight destination qualifiers for safe prediction gating.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compare resolved JALR next PC against the decode prediction, suppress correct duplicate redirects, and retain existing EX recovery for mismatches and unpredicted returns.\"\n","additions":34,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778695302632,"end":1778695302639}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09ce06156e3345bf016a04bc6f785c819993f5ddc778b4d06e"}},"id":"prt_e228013c7001NsvihoAcpNWAbk","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","messageID":"msg_e227f7006001PZZz2q8AtQDJLQ"}}
