{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778695309487,"sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_qj9sjT7yu273S3GaRVf8RLo6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_medium-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n2: title: \"Decode return target predictor\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   Prior predictor attempts for this core mostly regressed because they added\n6:   target adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack state, or predicted-PC\n7:   muxes directly to the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX\n8:   redirect penalty on every canonical function return, and CoreMark contains\n9:   enough call/return traffic that recovering one redirect cycle there may help\n10:   iterations per cycle. A return predictor that operates only after decode can\n11:   use the already-fetched instruction, regfile read data, and existing immediate\n12:   path while keeping fetch's common pc+4 path untouched.\n13: hypothesis: |\n14:   Add a decode-stage predictor for canonical returns only: legal JALR with\n15:   rd=x0, funct3=0, imm=0, and rs1=x1 or x5. ID computes the return target from\n16:   the already-read link register value and redirects fetch one cycle before EX\n17:   would, but only when the base register is not the destination of an unresolved\n18:   older instruction in ID/EX or EX/MEM. Carry a minimal predicted-valid and\n19:   predicted-next-PC field into ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal JALR redirect\n20:   on an exact match and uses the existing recovery redirect on mismatches. This\n21:   avoids the failed IF-side RAS/BTB/BTFNT machinery while targeting a narrower\n22:   control-flow pattern with no branch direction ambiguity.\n23: expected_impact:\n24:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n25:   confidence: low\n26: changes:\n27:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n28:     description: \"Add minimal predicted-valid and predicted-next-PC metadata to the ID/EX bundle for decode-stage return prediction validation.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Detect canonical JALR returns, compute the register-based target from rs1_data plus zero immediate, and emit early redirect metadata only when the base operand is safe.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n32:     description: \"Wire ID-stage return prediction redirect into the existing IF/hazard redirect path and provide in-flight destination qualifiers for safe prediction gating.\"\n33:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n34:     description: \"Compare resolved JALR next PC against the decode prediction, suppress correct duplicate redirects, and retain existing EX recovery for mismatches and unpredicted returns.\"\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\ntitle: \"Decode return target predictor\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  Prior predictor attempts for this core mostly regressed because they added\n  target adders, tag compares, counters, return-stack state, or predicted-PC\n  muxes directly to the IF next-PC path. The current core still pays the EX\n  redirect penalty on every canonical function return, and CoreMark contains\n  enough call/return traffic that recovering one redirect cycle there may help\n  iterations per cycle. A return predictor that operates only after decode can\n  use the already-fetched instruction, regfile read data, and existing immediate\n  path while keeping fetch's common pc+4 path untouched.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a decode-stage predictor for canonical returns only: legal JALR with\n  rd=x0, funct3=0, imm=0, and rs1=x1 or x5. ID computes the return target from\n  the already-read link register value and redirects fetch one cycle before EX\n  would, but only when the base register is not the destination of an unresolved\n  older instruction in ID/EX or EX/MEM. Carry a minimal predicted-valid and\n  predicted-next-PC field into ID/EX so EX suppresses the normal JALR redirect\n  on an exact match and uses the existing recovery redirect on mismatches. This","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778695309481,"end":1778695309486}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f343aa5157266ce016a04bc8bf528819b886f3dfa6126695c"}},"id":"prt_e22808320001vGOOvqLdfuhLg8","sessionID":"ses_1dd80c2a1fferEwtpnc0oLdwB4","messageID":"msg_e22806f91001Qwz8nq8B9KaDgi"}}
